<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali rahvusvaheline klassifikatsioon </eesti>
<inglise>International classification of explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjalid kuuluvad ohtlikkuse j&auml;rgi veol ja hoidmisel ohtlike ainete rahvusvahelise klassifikatsiooni alusel esimesse ohuklassi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) According to the hazard they present during carriage and storage, explosive substances belong to the first hazard division on the basis of the international classification of hazardous substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali veol tekkida v&otilde;iva avarii iseloomule vastavalt jaotatakse l&otilde;hkematerjalid kuude allklassi: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) According to the nature of potential accidents during the carriage of explosive substances, explosive substances are divided into six subdivisions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) allklass 1.1 - ained ja tooted, mille erip&auml;raks on v&otilde;ime plahvatada kogu massiga, s.o. hetkeliselt plahvatab kogu veosel olev l&otilde;hkematerjal; </eesti>
<inglise>1) subdivision 1.1 - substances and articles which have a mass explosion hazard, which means that the entire load of explosive substances explodes virtually instantaneously; </inglise>
<eesti>2) allklass 1.2 - ained ja tooted, mis ei plahvata kogu massiga, vaid nad paiskuvad plahvatusel laiali, kahjustades &uuml;mbritsevat keskkonda (objekte); </eesti>
<inglise>2) subdivision 1.2 - substances and articles which have a projection hazard, through which the surrounding environment (site) may be damaged, but not a mass explosion hazard; </inglise>
<eesti>3) allklass 1.3 - ained ja tooted, mis p&otilde;lemisel eraldavad suurel hulgal soojuskiirgust v&otilde;i s&uuml;ttivad &uuml;ksteise j&auml;rel v&auml;ikeste plahvatusefektidega v&otilde;i laialipaiskumisega v&otilde;i esinevad need efektid koos; </eesti>
<inglise>3) subdivision 1.3 - substances and articles, the combustion of which gives rise to considerable radiant heat or which burn one after another, producing minor blast or projection effects or both; </inglise>
<eesti>4) allklass 1.4 - ained ja tooted, mis v&otilde;ivad s&uuml;ttimisel v&otilde;i initsieerimisel ainult osaliselt plahvatada. </eesti>
<inglise>4) subdivision 1.4 - substances and articles which may explode only partially in the event of ignition or initiation. </inglise>
<eesti>Plahvatus toimub &uuml;ldjuhul ainult mingis konkreetses pakendis ega kandu edasi teistele pakenditele. </eesti>
<inglise>The explosion is generally confined to a specific package and does not spread to other packages. </inglise>
<eesti>Pakendi sisu laialipaiskumine on v&auml;het&otilde;en&auml;oline. </eesti>
<inglise>No projection of the contents of the package is to be expected. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lispidine tuli (kuumutamine) ei p&otilde;hjusta pakendi sisu hetkelist plahvatust; </eesti>
<inglise>An external fire (heating) does not cause virtually instantaneous explosion of the contents of the package; </inglise>
<eesti>5) allklass 1.5 - massiplahvatusohtlikud ained, mis on niiv&otilde;rd tuimad, et normaalsetel veotingimustel on nende initsieerumine v&otilde;i p&otilde;lemise &uuml;leminek plahvatuseks v&auml;het&otilde;en&auml;oline. </eesti>
<inglise>5) subdivision 1.5 - substances having a mass explosion hazard which are so insensitive that there is very little probability of initiation or of transition from burning to detonation under normal conditions of carriage. </inglise>
<eesti>Need ained ei tohi plahvatada tulekindluse katsetel; </eesti>
<inglise>Such substances must not explode in an external fire test; </inglise>
<eesti>6) allklass 1.6 - &uuml;liv&auml;ikese tundlikkusega massiplahvatusohutud tooted. </eesti>
<inglise>6) subdivision 1.6 - extremely insensitive articles which do not have a mass explosion hazard. </inglise>
<eesti>Need tooted sisaldavad &auml;&auml;rmiselt tuimi l&otilde;hkeaineid ja nende initsieerimine v&otilde;i selle levimise t&otilde;en&auml;osus on t&uuml;hiselt v&auml;ike. </eesti>
<inglise>Such articles contain extremely insensitive explosive substances and the probability of their initiation or of such initiation spreading is insignificant. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Koosveo ja kooshoiu v&otilde;imalikkuse j&auml;rgi jaotatakse l&otilde;hkematerjalid j&auml;rgmistesse sobivusr&uuml;hmadesse: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Explosive substances are divided into the following compatibility groups according to the possibility of mixed carriage and storage thereof: </inglise>
<eesti>1) A - initsieeriv l&otilde;hkeaine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) A - primary explosive substance; </inglise>
<eesti>2) B - initsieerivat l&otilde;hkeainet sisaldav toode, millel on v&auml;hem kui kaks efektiivset kaitseseadist. </eesti>
<inglise>2) B - article containing a primary explosive substance and not having two or more effective protective features. </inglise>
<eesti>Siia r&uuml;hma kuuluvad ka kahjustust&ouml;&ouml;deks etten&auml;htud detonaatorid, detonaatorite rakised ja s&uuml;tikud, isegi siis, kui nad ei sisalda initsieerivaid l&otilde;hkeaineid; </eesti>
<inglise>Detonators, detonator shells and fuse heads intended for demolition work belong to this group even if they do not contain a primary explosive substance; </inglise>
<eesti>3) C - paiske- ja v&auml;ljap&otilde;lev l&otilde;hkeaine v&otilde;i seda l&otilde;hkeainet sisaldav toode; </eesti>
<inglise>3) C - propellant explosive substance or other deflagrating explosive substance, or article containing such explosive substance; </inglise>
<eesti>4) D - brisantl&otilde;hkeaine, must p&uuml;ssirohi v&otilde;i brisantl&otilde;hkeainet sisaldav toode, milles ei ole initsieerimisvahendit, ja paiskelaengut v&otilde;i brisantl&otilde;hkeainet sisaldav toode, millel on v&auml;hemalt kaks efektiivset kaitseseadist; </eesti>
<inglise>4) D - high explosives, black powder or article containing a high explosive, in each case without means of initiation and without a propelling charge, or article containing a high explosive and having two or more effective protective features; </inglise>
<eesti>5) E - brisantl&otilde;hkeainet sisaldav toode, milles puuduvad initsieerimisvahendid, kuid on paiskelaeng (paiskelaengus ei v&otilde;i olla kergestis&uuml;ttivat vedelikku, geeli ega ises&uuml;ttivat vedelikku) v&otilde;i puudub paiskelaeng; </eesti>
<inglise>5) E - article containing a high explosive, without means of initiation, with a propelling charge (other than one containing an inflammable liquid or gel or a hypergolic liquid) or without a propelling charge; </inglise>
<eesti>6) F - brisantl&otilde;hkeainet, initsieerimisvahendit ja paiskelaengut sisaldav v&otilde;i ilma sellise laenguta toode (paiskelaengus ei v&otilde;i olla kergestis&uuml;ttivat vedelikku, geeli ega ises&uuml;ttivat vedelikku); </eesti>
<inglise>6) F - article containing a high explosive, with its own means of initiation, with a propelling charge (other than one containing an inflammable liquid or gel or a hypergolic liquid) or without a propelling charge; </inglise>
<eesti>7) G - p&uuml;rotehniline aine v&otilde;i toode, mis sisaldab nii p&uuml;rotehnilist ainet kui ka valgusttekitavat, s&uuml;&uuml;tavat, pisaraid v&otilde;i suitsu tekitavat komponenti (ei tohi sisaldada vett aktiviseerivat toodet, valget fosforit, fosfiide ega p&uuml;rofoorset ainet, kergesti- v&otilde;i ises&uuml;ttivat vedelikku v&otilde;i geeli); </eesti>
<inglise>7) G - pyrotechnic substance, or article containing both a pyrotechnic substance and an illuminating, incendiary, tear- or smoke-producing substance (other than a water-activated article or one which contains white phosphorus, phosphides, a pyrophoric substance, an inflammable or hypergolic liquid or gel); </inglise>
<eesti>8) H - toode, mis sisaldab nii l&otilde;hkeainet kui ka valget fosforit; </eesti>
<inglise>8) H - article containing both an explosive substance and white phosphorus; </inglise>
<eesti>9) I - toode, mis sisaldab nii l&otilde;hkeainet kui ka kergestis&uuml;ttivat vedelikku v&otilde;i geeli; </eesti>
<inglise>9) I - article containing both an explosive substance and an inflammable liquid or gel; </inglise>
<eesti>10) K - toode, mis sisaldab nii l&otilde;hkeainet kui ka m&uuml;rkkemikaali; </eesti>
<inglise>10) K - article containing both an explosive substance and a toxic chemical agent; </inglise>
<eesti>11) L - l&otilde;hkematerjal, mis sisaldab vett aktiviseerivat eriti ohtlikku l&otilde;hkeainet v&otilde;i milles on ises&uuml;ttivaid vedelikke, fosfiide v&otilde;i p&uuml;rofoorseid aineid, mist&otilde;ttu iga aine tuleb omaette isoleerida; </eesti>
<inglise>11) L - explosive substance containing a water-activated explosive substance presenting a special risk, or containing hypergolic liquids, phosphides or pyrophoric substances and necessitating isolation of each substance; </inglise>
<eesti>12) N - eriti v&auml;ikese tundlikkusega l&otilde;hkeainet sisaldav toode; </eesti>
<inglise>12) N - article containing an extremely insensitive explosive substance; </inglise>
<eesti>13) S - aine v&otilde;i toode, mis on sellise ehitusega v&otilde;i selliselt pakitud, et mistahes ohtlikud efektid toimuvad pakendi vigastumisel ainult pakendis. </eesti>
<inglise>13) S - substance or article so packed or designed that any hazardous effects upon damage to the package are confined within the package. </inglise>
<eesti>Plahvatusefekt v&otilde;i laialipaiskumine tulekahjus on niiv&otilde;rd v&auml;ikesed, et oluliselt ei takista tulekustutust&ouml;id ega muude ekstreemabin&otilde;ude rakendamist pakendi vahetus l&auml;heduses. </eesti>
<inglise>Blast or projection effects in the case of a fire are limited to the extent that they do not significantly hinder or prevent fire-fighting or other emergency response efforts in the immediate vicinity of the package. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) For the purposes of this Act: </inglise>
<eesti>1) l&otilde;hkeaine - keemiline &uuml;hend v&otilde;i ainete mehaaniline segu, mis v&otilde;ib termilise m&otilde;jutuse (kuumutamine, s&auml;de), mehaanilise m&otilde;jutuse (l&ouml;&ouml;k, surve, h&otilde;&otilde;rdumine), keemilise reaktsiooni v&otilde;i teise aine detonatsiooni toimel plahvatada &otilde;huhapnikku kasutamata; </eesti>
<inglise>1) "explosive" means a chemical compound or a mechanical mixture of substances that may explode without the presence of free oxygen due to thermal impact (heating, spark), mechanical impact (shock, pressure, friction), chemical reaction, or detonation of other substances; </inglise>
<eesti>2) paiskel&otilde;hkeaine - l&otilde;hkeaine, mille detonatsioonikiirus on kuni 2000 m/s ja mis plahvatusel paiskab keskkonna laiali; </eesti>
<inglise>2) "propellant explosive substance" means an explosive with a detonation velocity of up to 2000 m/s and which demolishes the surrounding environment upon explosion; </inglise>
<eesti>3) brisantl&otilde;hkeaine - l&otilde;hkeaine, mille detonatsioonikiirus on &uuml;le 2000 m/s ja mis plahvatusel purustab keskkonda ja paiskab selle laiali; </eesti>
<inglise>3) "high explosive" means an explosive with a detonation velocity greater than 2000 m/s and which destroys and demolishes the surrounding environment upon explosion; </inglise>
<eesti>4) initsieeriv l&otilde;hkeaine - l&otilde;hkeaine, mis plahvatab s&uuml;ttimisel, kergest l&ouml;&ouml;gist v&otilde;i detonatsioonist ja mille v&auml;ikese koguse plahvatus kutsub esile teise l&otilde;hkeaine plahvatuse; </eesti>
<inglise>4) "primary explosive substance" means an explosive which explodes upon ignition or from a light shock or detonation, and the explosion of a small amount of which induces an explosion in other explosives; </inglise>
<eesti>5) p&uuml;rotehniline aine - s&uuml;&uuml;tav, signaali, ilutulestikku, suitsu tekitav jms. aine, mis plahvatab v&otilde;i p&otilde;leb &otilde;huhapnikku kasutamata, tekitades valgust, soojust, heli, suitsu, gaasi v&otilde;i muid n&auml;htusi. </eesti>
<inglise>5) "pyrotechnic substance" means an incendiary substance or a substance which produces signals, fireworks, smoke etc., which explodes or burns without the presence of free oxygen producing light, heat, sound, smoke, gas or other phenomena. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) P&uuml;rotehnilised tooted jaotatakse neis oleva p&uuml;rotehnilise aine koguse, omaduste ja kasutusotstarbe j&auml;rgi j&auml;rgmistesse klassidesse: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Pyrotechnic articles are divided into the following divisions, according to the amount, characteristics and purpose of pyrotechnic substances contained therein: </inglise>
<eesti>I klass - m&auml;nguilutulestik (p&uuml;rotehniliste ainete lubatav &uuml;ldmass tootes kuni kolm grammi ja paiskelaengu puudumine); </eesti>
<inglise>division I - toy fireworks (the permissible total mass of pyrotechnic substances in the article is up to 3 grams, and there shall be no propelling charge); </inglise>
<eesti>II klass - v&auml;ike ilutulestik (p&uuml;rotehnilise aine lubatav &uuml;ldmass tootes kuni 50 grammi, komplekttootes v&otilde;ib &uuml;ldmass olla kuni 250 grammi); </eesti>
<inglise>division II - small fireworks (the permissible total mass of pyrotechnic substance in the article is up to 50 grams, and the total mass of pyrotechnic substances in a set of articles may be up to 250 grams); </inglise>
<eesti>III klass - keskmine ilutulestik (p&uuml;rotehniliste ainete lubatav &uuml;ldmass tootes kuni 250 grammi, komplekttootes v&otilde;ib &uuml;ldmass olla kuni 1200 grammi); </eesti>
<inglise>division III - medium fireworks (the permissible total mass of pyrotechnic substances in the article is up to 250 grams, and the total mass of pyrotechnic substances in a set of articles may be up to 1200 grams); </inglise>
<eesti>IV klass - suur ilutulestik (p&uuml;rotehniliste ainete &uuml;ldmass tootes ei ole piiratud); </eesti>
<inglise>division IV - large fireworks (the permissible total mass of pyrotechnic substances in the article is not limited); </inglise>
<eesti>T klass - tehnilise otstarbe p&uuml;rotehnika: </eesti>
<inglise>division T - pyrotechnics for technical purposes: </inglise>
<eesti>1) allklass T1 - peamiselt siseruumides kasutatav lavap&uuml;rotehnika, kus p&uuml;rotehnilise efektiga ei kaasne m&uuml;rgiste gaaside, s&ouml;&ouml;bivate ainete ja raskete, teravnurksete ning kuumade lenduvate osakeste teke; </eesti>
<inglise>1) subdivision T1 - stage pyrotechnics mainly used in interior spaces where the pyrotechnic effect does not result in the creation of toxic gases, caustic substances or heavy, sharp or hot volatile particles; </inglise>
<eesti>2) allklass T2 - h&auml;dasignaalivahendid ja p&uuml;rotehniline laskemoon. </eesti>
<inglise>2) subdivision T2 - distress signal equipment and pyrotechnic ammunition. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.10.2001 entered into force 01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </inglise>
<eesti>(5 (1)) Pauguti on paberist v&otilde;i plastmassist kesta paigutatud I v&otilde;i II klassi kuuluv p&uuml;rotehniline toode, mille kasutamise eesm&auml;rk on laengu s&uuml;ttimisel heliefekti (paugu) tekitamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(5 (1)) A cracker is a pyrotechnic article of division I or II placed in a paper or plastic shell; the aim of use of such article is the creation of a sound effect (a cracking sound) upon the ignition of the charge. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.10.2001 entered into force 01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Tsiviilk&auml;ibe l&otilde;hkematerjalid v&otilde;ivad kuuluda k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud 1.1, 1.4, 1.5 ja 1.6 allklassi ning k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud B, C, D, E, F, G ja S sobivusr&uuml;hma. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Explosive substances used for civilian purposes may belong to subdivisions 1.1, 1.4, 1.5 and 1.6 provided for in subsection (2) of this section, and to compatibility groups B, C, D, E, F, G and S provided for in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) L&otilde;hkematerjali allklassi number koos sobivusr&uuml;hma t&auml;hega on selle l&otilde;hkeaine klassifikatsiooni kood, mis peab olema kantud l&otilde;hkeaine pakendile ja l&otilde;hkeainet transportivale veokile paigaldatavatele ohum&auml;rgistele. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The number of the subdivision of an explosive substance and the letter signifying its compatibility group comprise the classification code of the explosive, which shall be indicated on the packaging of the explosive and on danger labels on vehicles transporting the explosive. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali tsiviilk&auml;ibesse lubamine </eesti>
<inglise>Permission to use explosive substances for civilian purposes </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tsiviilk&auml;ibes v&otilde;ib kasutada l&otilde;hkematerjali, mille kohta on v&auml;lja antud alaline v&otilde;i ajutine kasutusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Explosive substances may be used for civilian purposes if a permanent or temporary permit of use has been issued therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali alalise ja ajutise kasutusloa v&auml;ljastab ja pikendab Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Temporary and permanent permits of use for explosive substances are issued and renewed by the Technical Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Alaline kasutusluba v&auml;ljastatakse t&auml;htajaga kuni 10 aastat ja seda v&otilde;idakse pikendada veel kuni 10 aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Permanent permits of use are issued for a term of up to ten years and may be renewed for up to ten years. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Alaline kasutusluba kaotab kehtivuse: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A permanent permit of use becomes invalid: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&auml;htaja l&otilde;ppemisel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) on the date of expiry; </inglise>
<eesti>2) l&otilde;hkematerjali tootmise l&otilde;petamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) upon discontinuation of the production of the explosive substance; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kui l&otilde;hkematerjali tsiviilk&auml;ive keelustatakse m&otilde;ne teise seaduse v&otilde;i rahvusvahelise kokkuleppega. </eesti>
<inglise>3) if the use of the explosive substance for civilian purposes is prohibited by another Act or international agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ajutine kasutusluba antakse kuni 100 tonni l&otilde;hkematerjali l&otilde;hkamiseks kuni kuue kuu jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Temporary permits of use are issued for the blasting of up to 100 tonnes of explosive substances during a period of up to six months. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Enne uue l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamist v&otilde;i sissevedu tuleb l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistajal v&otilde;i sissevedajal (edaspidi tarnija) l&auml;bi viia katsel&otilde;hkamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Prior to the manufacture or import of a new explosive substance, the manufacturer or importer (hereinafter supplier) of the explosive substance shall conduct test blasting. </inglise>
<eesti>Katsel&otilde;hkamisega kontrollitakse l&otilde;hkematerjali sobivust antud geoloogilistes ja h&uuml;drogeoloogilistes tingimustes kasutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>The suitability of an explosive substance for use under given geological and hydrogeological conditions is assessed by test blasting. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Katsel&otilde;hkamise l&auml;biviimiseks tuleb taotleda l&otilde;hkematerjali ajutist kasutusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A temporary permit of use for explosive substances shall be applied for in order to conduct test blasting. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Katsetatav l&otilde;hkematerjal peab olema eelnevalt laboratoorselt kontrollitud Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni poolt tunnustatud laboratooriumis ja oma koostise, omaduste ning pakendiga tagama ohutu k&auml;sitsemise ja veo. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) An explosive substance to be tested shall undergo prior assessment in a laboratory recognised by the Technical Inspectorate, and the composition, characteristics and packaging of the explosive substance shall ensure safe handling and carriage. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Sisseveetava l&otilde;hkematerjali laboratoorne kontroll ei ole n&otilde;utav, kui on Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni otsus l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistaja asukohaj&auml;rgse riigi p&auml;deva organi antud kasutusloa tunnustamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) Laboratory assessment of an imported explosive substance is not required if the Technical Inspectorate resolves to recognise a permit of use issued by the competent authority of the state in which the manufacturer of the explosive substance is seated. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) Katsel&otilde;hkamist juhib kasutusloa taotleja moodustatud komisjon, kelle liikmeks on ka Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni ja tarnija esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) Test blasting is directed by a committee formed by the applicant for a permit of use, the members of which shall include a representative of the Technical Inspectorate and a representative of the supplier. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui katsel&otilde;hkamisega on saavutatud n&otilde;utav tulemus, v&otilde;ib l&otilde;hkematerjali tarnija taotleda alalist kasutusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>A supplier of explosive substances may apply for a permanent permit of use if test blasting achieves the required result. </inglise>
<eesti>(11) P&otilde;levkivikaevanduse tarbeks valmistatava l&otilde;hkeaine puhul tuleb selle tolmuplahvatusohutus eelnevalt m&auml;&auml;rata katsestrekis Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni poolt esitatud skeemi kohaselt ja tema esindaja juuresolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(11) The dust explosion safety of explosives manufactured for the purposes of oil shale mining shall be determined beforehand in a test drift according to a plan provided by the Technical Inspectorate and in the presence of a representative thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Katsestrekk on kindla l&auml;bim&otilde;&otilde;duga metalltoru, kus luuakse tolmuplahvatust soodustavad, kaevanduses esineda v&otilde;ivad ekstreemsed tingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>A test drift is a metal tube with a fixed diameter, where extreme conditions promoting a dust explosion, similar to those which may occur in a mine, are created. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&otilde;levkivitolm etteantud skeemi kohaselt l&auml;biviidud l&otilde;hkamisel ei plahvata, v&otilde;ib tarnija taotleda l&otilde;hkeaine ajutist kasutusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>A supplier may apply for a temporary permit of use if oil shale dust does not explode upon blasting carried out according to the prescribed plan. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Eesti l&otilde;hkematerjaliregister </eesti>
<inglise>Estonian Register of Explosive Substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjal, mille kohta on v&auml;lja antud alaline kasutusluba, kantakse riiklikusse l&otilde;hkematerjaliregistrisse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Explosive substances for which permanent permits of use are issued shall be entered in the state explosive substances register. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riikliku l&otilde;hkematerjaliregistri asutab Vabariigi Valitsus andmekogude seadusega (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597; 2001, 7, 17; 17, 77) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The state explosive substances register shall be established by the Government of the Republic pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Databases Act (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597; 2001, 7, 17; 17, 77). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Plastiline l&otilde;hkeaine </eesti>
<inglise>Plastic explosives </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Plastiline l&otilde;hkeaine on suure v&otilde;imsusega l&otilde;hkeaine, mis normaalsel toatemperatuuril on voolitav v&otilde;i elastne. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Plastic explosives are high volume explosives which, at normal room temperature, can be moulded or are elastic. </inglise>
<eesti>Plastiline l&otilde;hkeaine peab olema m&auml;rgistatud. </eesti>
<inglise>Plastic explosives shall be marked. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on l&otilde;hkeaine m&auml;rgistamine kerglenduvate indikaatorainete manustamine l&otilde;hkeainele tema avastamise v&otilde;imaldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, the marking of explosives means the addition of vaporising detection agents to explosives to enable the detection of the explosives. </inglise>
<eesti>Indikaatoraine ja selle sisaldus l&otilde;hkeaines on m&auml;&auml;ratletud rahvusvaheliste lepetega. </eesti>
<inglise>Detection agents and their content in explosives are determined by international agreements. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Plastilise l&otilde;hkeaine kasutamine tsiviilk&auml;ibes on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The use of plastic explosives for civilian purposes is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Erandina v&otilde;ib plastilist l&otilde;hkeainet tsiviilk&auml;ibes kasutada kaitseministri loal. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) As an exception, plastic explosives may be used for civilian purposes with the permission of the Minister of Defence. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotlus plastilise l&otilde;hkeaine saamiseks ja kasutamiseks esitatakse kaitseministrile koosk&otilde;lastatult Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooniga. </eesti>
<inglise>Applications for the receipt and use of plastic explosives shall be submitted to the Minister of Defence in concordance with the Technical Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Manufacture of Explosive Substances </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Activity licence for manufacture of explosive substance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamiseks (edaspidi l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamisluba) v&auml;ljastab Majandusministeerium koosk&otilde;lastatult Politseiameti, Tervisekaitseinspektsiooni ja Keskkonnaministeeriumiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Activity licences for the manufacture of an explosive substance (hereinafter permits for the manufacture of an explosive substance) are issued by the Ministry of Economic Affairs in concordance with the Police Administration, Health Protection Inspectorate and Ministry of the Environment. </inglise>
<eesti>Politseiamet, Tervisekaitseinspektsioon ja Keskkonnaministeerium langetavad otsuse koosk&otilde;lastuse kohta avalduse saamisest 30 p&auml;eva jooksul ning v&otilde;ivad koosk&otilde;lastusest keelduda, kui l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamine kahjustaks inimeste julgeolekut v&otilde;i looduskeskkonda v&otilde;i ei vasta tervisekaitse- v&otilde;i h&uuml;gieenin&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>The Police Administration, Health Protection Inspectorate and Ministry of the Environment shall render a decision concerning concordance within thirty days after receipt of an application, and may refuse concordance if the manufacture of the explosive substance would jeopardise the security of people or damage the natural environment, or if the manufacture of an explosive substance does not comply with health protection or hygiene requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamine tegevus, mille tulemusena valmib l&otilde;hkematerjal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, the manufacture of an explosive substance is any activity resulting in the production of an explosive substance. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;iste sisaldab l&otilde;hke- v&otilde;i p&uuml;rotehnilise aine vormimist, t&ouml;&ouml;tlemist, segamist omavahel v&otilde;i muude komponentidega, l&otilde;hkematerjali v&otilde;i p&uuml;rotehnilise toote pakkimist v&otilde;i paigutamist l&otilde;hkamisvahendisse. </eesti>
<inglise>The term includes the moulding, processing and mixing of explosives or pyrotechnic substances with one another or with other substances, and the packaging of explosive and pyrotechnic articles and the placement thereof into blasting supplies. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lihtl&otilde;hkeaine valmistamisloa v&auml;ljastab Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon, kui lihtl&otilde;hkeainet valmistatakse oma vajadusteks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A permit for the manufacture of a blasting agent is issued by the Technical Inspectorate if the blasting agent is manufactured for use only by the manufacturer. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on lihtl&otilde;hkeaine puhta granuleeritud ammooniumnitraadi ja vedela v&otilde;i tahke p&otilde;levkomponendi segamisel moodustuv l&otilde;hkeaine. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) For the purposes of this Act, a blasting agent is an explosive formed by the mixing of pure granulated ammonium nitrate with a liquid or solid combustible agent. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Lihtl&otilde;hkeaine valmistamisel mitmele tarbijale koos l&otilde;hkeaine padrundamise ja pakendamisega v&auml;ljastatakse lihtl&otilde;hkeaine valmistamisluba vastavalt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A permit for the manufacture of a blasting agent shall be issued according to the provisions of subsection (1) of this section upon the manufacture of the blasting agent for several consumers together with cartridging and packaging of the blasting agent. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjalitehas </eesti>
<inglise>Explosive substances plant </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali v&otilde;ib valmistada ainult selleks otstarbeks ehitatud v&otilde;i renoveeritud tehases. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Explosive substances may be manufactured only in plants built or renovated for such purpose. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjalitehas on k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes ehitiste ja rajatiste kompleks, mis on vajalik l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, an explosive substances plant is a complex of structures and constructions necessary for the manufacture of explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkematerjalitehase ehitusluba taotletakse kohalikult omavalitsuselt vastavalt planeerimis- ja ehitusseadusele (RT I 1995, 59, 1006; 1996, 36, 738; 49, 953; 1999, 27, 380; 29, 398 ja 399; 95, 843; 2000, 54, 348; 2001, 42, 234; 50, 283; 65, 377). </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Building permits for explosive substances plants shall be applied for from the local government in accordance with the Planning and Building Act (RT I 1995, 59, 1006; 1996, 36, 738; 49, 953; 1999, 27, 380; 29, 398 and 399; 95, 843; 2000, 54, 348; 2001, 42, 234; 50, 283; 65, 377). </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ehitusloa taotlusele lisatakse t&auml;iendavalt l&otilde;hkematerjalitehase ja selle juurde kuuluva l&otilde;hkematerjalilao asukoha ja neid &uuml;mbritseva maa-ala plaan (m&otilde;&otilde;tkavas kuni 1: 20000), mis h&otilde;lmab tehase ja lao ohtliku ala suurima mahuga hoidla plahvatusel tekkiva &otilde;hu l&ouml;&ouml;klaine j&auml;rgi ning kuhu on kantud sellesse alasse j&auml;&auml;vad ehitised, teed jm. ning m&auml;rgitud nende otstarve. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A plan of the site of an explosive substances plant, explosive substances stores belonging to the plant and the surrounding area (on a scale of up to 1: 20 000) shall be appended to an application for a building permit, including the danger zone of the plant and stores determined by the shockwave which would result from an explosion of the largest magazine, and indication of the structures and roads etc. falling within such area and the purpose thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on ohtlik ala maa-ala l&otilde;hkematerjalitehase, l&otilde;hkematerjalilao v&otilde;i l&otilde;hkekoha &uuml;mber, kus plahvatus v&otilde;ib avaldada kahjustavat toimet elusolendile v&otilde;i seal paiknevale ehitisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) For the purposes of this Act, a danger zone means an area surrounding an explosive substances plant, explosive substances store or blasting site, where an explosion may damage living beings or structures situated in the area. </inglise>
<eesti>Ohtliku ala ulatus m&auml;&auml;ratakse projekti v&otilde;i passiga. </eesti>
<inglise>The extent of a danger zone is determined by a plan or the blasting pattern. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Ehitusj&auml;relevalvet l&otilde;hkematerjalitehase ehitusel teostab planeerimis- ja ehitusseaduse kohaselt kohalik omavalitsus, Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;kaitseseaduse (RT 1992, 25, 343; RT I 1996, 49, 953) kohaselt T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsioon ning tervisekaitse-, keskkonnakaitse- ja tulet&otilde;rjealast ning tehnilist j&auml;relevalvet aga vastavate riigiasutuste esindajad. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Construction supervision over the construction of an explosive substances plant is exercised pursuant to the Planning and Building Act by the local government and pursuant to the Republic of Estonia Labour Protection Act (RT 1992, 25, 343; RT I 1996, 49, 953) by the Labour Inspectorate; health protection, environmental protection, fire fighting and technical supervision is exercised by representatives of the appropriate state agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjalitehase kasutuselev&otilde;tt </eesti>
<inglise>Use of explosive substances plant </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjalitehase kasutuselev&otilde;tmiseks peab tehase omanik v&otilde;i valdaja saama kohalikult omavalitsuselt ehitise kasutusloa ja esitama Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioonile kirjaliku avalduse l&otilde;hkematerjalitehase kasutuselev&otilde;tmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to use an explosive substances plant, the owner or possessor of the plant shall obtain a permit for the use of the structure from the local government, and submit a written application to the Technical Inspectorate for the use of the explosive substances plant. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Esitatud avaldusest l&auml;htudes moodustab Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon tehase tehnilise vastuv&otilde;tukomisjoni (edaspidi komisjon), m&auml;&auml;rates selle koosseisu &uuml;he oma t&ouml;&ouml;tajatest ning koosk&otilde;lastatult vastava asutusega politseiprefektuuri, tulet&otilde;rjej&auml;relevalve, Kaitseministeeriumi, Keskkonnaministeeriumi, Tervisekaitseinspektsiooni, T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni ja kohaliku omavalitsuse esindajad. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Technical Inspectorate shall form a technical approval committee (hereinafter committee) on the basis of a submitted application, appoint one of its employees to the membership of the committee and, in concordance with the corresponding agency, appoint a representative of the Police Prefecture, fire fighting supervisory body, Ministry of Defence, Ministry of the Environment, Health Protection Inspectorate, Labour Protection Inspectorate and the local government. </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjoni esimeheks on Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>The representative of the Technical Inspectorate shall be the chairman of the committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Komisjon tuleb kokku kutsuda hiljemalt &uuml;he kuu jooksul p&auml;rast avalduse esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The committee shall be convened within one month after the submission of the application. </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjoni kokkukutsumise t&auml;htajast teatatakse komisjoni liikmetele ja tehase omanikule v&otilde;i valdajale v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat enne kokkukutsumise t&auml;htaega. </eesti>
<inglise>The members of the committee and the owner or possessor of the plant shall be informed of the date the committee is convened not less than two weeks prior to such date. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Komisjoni poolt l&auml;biviidud kontrolli tulemuste p&otilde;hjal koostatakse tehase k&auml;itamise akt, millele kirjutavad alla k&otilde;ik kontrollimises osalenud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A statement on the operation of a plant shall be prepared on the basis of the results of the inspection carried out by the committee, and signed by every person who participates in the inspection. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;itamise akt on l&otilde;hkematerjalitehase k&auml;itamisloa v&auml;ljaandmise aluseks. </eesti>
<inglise>An operation statement constitutes the basis for the issue of an operation permit for a plant. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui komisjon leiab kontrollimisel m&otilde;ningaid puudusi, mis ei avalda m&otilde;ju tootmistehnoloogiale ega suurenda ohtu l&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemisel, v&otilde;ib k&auml;itamise aktile lisada ettekirjutuse konkreetsete puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks kindlaks t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If, upon inspection, the committee finds any omissions which do not influence production technology or increase hazards in the handling of explosive substances, a precept for the elimination of specified omissions by a specified date may be added to the operation statement. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Akti &uuml;ks eksemplar antakse k&otilde;ikidele kontrollimisel osalenutele, samuti tehase omanikule v&otilde;i valdajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Each person who participates in the inspection and the owner or possessor of the plant shall receive one original copy of the statement. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui kasutusele v&otilde;etakse vaid osa l&otilde;hkematerjalitehasest, m&auml;rgitakse see akti. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If only one part of an explosive substances plant is used, such fact shall be included in the statement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjalitehase k&auml;itamisluba </eesti>
<inglise>Operation permit for explosive substances plant </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;itamise akti alusel annab Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon l&otilde;hkematerjalitehase omanikule v&otilde;i valdajale k&auml;itamisloa. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Technical Inspectorate issues an operation permit to the owner or possessor of an explosive substances plant on the basis of an operation statement. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;itamisloa &auml;rakirjad saadetakse kahe n&auml;dala jooksul komisjoni t&ouml;&ouml;s osalenud ja ehitusj&auml;relevalvet teostanud asutustele. </eesti>
<inglise>Copies of an operation permit shall be sent within two weeks to the agencies which participated in the work of the committee and exercised construction supervision. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Enne k&auml;itamisloa v&auml;ljaandmist v&otilde;ib Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon anda l&otilde;hkematerjalitehase v&otilde;i selle osa proovik&auml;itamisloa. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Prior to the issue of an operation permit, the Technical Inspectorate may issue a test operation permit for an explosive substances plant or a part thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Proovik&auml;itamisluba antakse seadmete katsetamiseks ja optimaalsesse t&ouml;&ouml;re&zcaron;iimi viimiseks kuni kolmeks kuuks. </eesti>
<inglise>A test operation permit is issued for up to three months to test equipment and find the optimal mode of operation. </inglise>
<eesti>Proovik&auml;itamisloa t&auml;htaja l&otilde;ppemisel v&otilde;etakse l&otilde;hkematerjalitehas kasutusele k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 8 s&auml;testatu kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the expiry of the test operation permit, the explosive substances plant shall be used pursuant to the provisions of &sect; 8 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkematerjalitehas ei tohi alustada proovik&auml;itamist ega t&ouml;&ouml;d enne, kui k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 29 kohaselt on m&auml;&auml;ratud l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamise eest vastutav(ad) isik(ud). </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An explosive substances plant shall not commence test operation or operation before the person or persons responsible for the manufacture of explosive substances are appointed pursuant to &sect; 29 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui l&otilde;hkematerjalitehast kavatsetakse laiendada v&otilde;i muuta tootmistehnoloogiat, tuleb taotleda uus k&auml;itamisluba k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an explosive substances plant is to be expanded or production technology is to be altered, a new operation permit shall be applied for pursuant to the procedure provided for in this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Lihtl&otilde;hkeaine valmistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Manufacture of blasting agents </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lihtl&otilde;hkeainet v&otilde;ib valmistada Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni loa alusel seadmetega, millele oli antud kasutusluba, l&otilde;hkeaine valmistamispunktis v&otilde;i l&otilde;hkeainesegistis-laadimismasinas t&ouml;&ouml;kohal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Blasting agents may be manufactured on the basis of a permit issued by the Technical Inspectorate with equipment for which a permit of use has been issued at a place of manufacture of explosives, or in mixing and loading equipment at a jobsite. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on l&otilde;hkeaine valmistamispunkt koht, kus paikneb statsionaarne v&otilde;i teisaldatav agregaat ammooniumnitraadi segamiseks vedelate v&otilde;i tahkete p&otilde;levkomponentidega koos l&auml;htekomponentide ladude ja abiseadmetega lihtl&otilde;hkeaine valmistamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, a place of manufacture of explosives is a place where stationary or mobile equipment for mixing ammonium nitrate with liquid or solid combustible agents, and stores for initial components and auxiliary equipment for the manufacture of blasting agents are located. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lihtl&otilde;hkeaine valmistamist ei tohi alustada enne, kui Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni esindaja koos T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni, politsei ja tulet&otilde;rjej&auml;relevalve esindajatega on kontrollinud l&otilde;hkeaine valmistamispunkti ja l&otilde;hkeainesegisteid-laadimismasinaid ning tuvastanud, et lihtl&otilde;hkeaine valmistamispunkti asukoht ja seadmed, samuti lihtl&otilde;hkeaine valmistamiseks kasutatava tooraine ladustamistingimused vastavad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 60 l&otilde;ike 1 kohaselt kehtestatud eeskirjan&otilde;uetele ning kui selleks on koosk&otilde;lastus Tervisekaitseinspektsioonilt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The manufacture of blasting agents shall not commence before a representative of the Technical Inspectorate together with representatives of the Labour Inspectorate, the Police and the firefighting supervisory body have inspected the place of manufacture of explosives or the mixing and loading equipment, and ascertained that the site of the place of manufacture, the equipment and the storage conditions of raw materials used for the manufacture of blasting agents comply with the requirements established pursuant to subsection 60 (1) of this Act, and the Health Protection Inspectorate has concorded commencement. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Lihtl&otilde;hkeainet v&otilde;ib valmistada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 30 kohaselt atesteeritud l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamise eest vastutava isiku juhtimisel vastavalt valmistamisjuhendile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Blasting agents may be manufactured under the direction of a person responsible for the manufacture of explosive substances if such person has passed an evaluation pursuant to &sect; 30 of this Act, and in accordance with the manufacturing instructions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjalitehase v&otilde;i l&otilde;hkeaine valmistamispunkti likvideerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Vacation of explosive substances plant or place of manufacture of explosives </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui l&otilde;hkematerjalitehas, selle osa v&otilde;i l&otilde;hkeaine valmistamispunkt likvideeritakse, teatab likvideeritava objekti omanik v&otilde;i valdaja sellest Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioonile viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast t&ouml;&ouml; l&otilde;petamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the vacation of an explosive substances plant, a part thereof or a place of manufacture of explosives, the owner or possessor of the site to be vacated shall inform the Technical Inspectorate of such vacation within five working days after termination of work. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjalitehase v&otilde;i l&otilde;hkeaine valmistamispunkti likvideerimise j&auml;rel peab likvideeritud objekti omanik v&otilde;i valdaja s&auml;ilitama vormikohaseid arvestusraamatuid v&auml;hemalt 10 aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The owner or possessor of a vacated explosive substances plant or place of manufacture of explosives shall preserve the ledgers thereof in prescribed form for not less than ten years after liquidation of the site. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjalitehase v&otilde;i l&otilde;hkeaine valmistamispunkti taask&auml;ivitamine v&otilde;i renoveerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Resumption of operations or renovation of explosive substances plant or place of manufacture of explosives </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamine l&otilde;hkematerjalitehases v&otilde;i selle osas on seiskunud &uuml;le &uuml;he aasta, tuleb taotleda uus k&auml;itamisluba vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 9 s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If the manufacture of explosive substances in an explosive substances plant or a part thereof has been suspended for more than one year, a new operation permit shall be applied for pursuant to the provisions of &sect; 9 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkeaine valmistamispunkti seiskumisel &uuml;le &uuml;he aasta v&otilde;ib seal t&ouml;&ouml;d taasalustada vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 10 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the suspension of operation of a place of manufacture of explosives for more than one year, the operation thereof may be resumed pursuant to the provisions of subsection 10 (3) of this Act </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&auml;heoluliste &uuml;mberehituste korral, kui renoveeritud seadmed on analoogsed endistega ning ei muutu tootmistehnoloogia ja ohutusn&otilde;uded, ei ole uus k&auml;itamisluba vajalik. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A new operation permit is not needed in the case of minor renovations if the renovated equipment is identical to the equipment formerly used and there is no change in production technology or safety requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>Tehtud muudatustest tuleb informeerida Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni. </eesti>
<inglise>The Technical Inspectorate shall be informed of any changes made. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;ive </eesti>
<inglise>Trade in Explosive Substances </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba l&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;giks </eesti>
<inglise>Activity licence for sale of explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusluba l&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;giks (edaspidi l&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;giluba) v&otilde;ib taotleda &auml;ri&uuml;hing, kelle p&otilde;hikirjas on l&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;mine tegevusalana ette n&auml;htud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A commercial undertaking whose articles of association prescribe the sale of explosive substances as one of its areas of activity may apply for an activity licence for the sale of explosive substances (hereinafter explosive substances sales permit). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;gilubasid annab v&auml;lja, muudab, peatab ning t&uuml;histab Politseiamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Explosive substances sales permits are issued, amended, suspended and revoked by the Police Administration. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;giluba v&otilde;ib v&auml;lja anda &auml;ri&uuml;hingule, kellel on olemas l&otilde;hkematerjaliladu v&otilde;i rendileping l&otilde;hkematerjalilao kasutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An explosive substances sales permit may be issued to a commercial undertaking which has an explosive substances store or a commercial lease contract for the use of an explosive substances store. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;giluba antakse t&auml;htajaga kuni viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Explosive substances sales permits are issued for a term of up to five years. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;giloa andmisest keeldumine </eesti>
<inglise>Refusal to issue explosive substances sales permit </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;giloa andmisest v&otilde;ib keelduda, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>Issue of an explosive substances sales permit may be refused if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) taotlejal ei ole piisavalt tehnilisi v&otilde;imalusi ega personali nimetatud tegevusalal tegutsemiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the applicant has inadequate technical capability or personnel for operation in the specified area of activity; </inglise>
<eesti>2) taotleja esitab tegelikkusele mittevastavat teavet; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the applicant provides inaccurate information; </inglise>
<eesti>3) taotlejal on olnud k&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i relvaseaduse ning nende alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide olulisi rikkumisi viimase kahe aasta jooksul; </eesti>
<inglise>3) within the two immediately preceding years, the applicant has been in material violation of this Act, the Weapons Act or legislation established on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>4) taotlejale varem v&auml;ljaantud l&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;giloa kehtetuks tunnistamisest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud v&auml;hem kui kaks aastat ja m&uuml;&uuml;giloa kehtetuks tunnistamine oli tingitud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 15 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 2, 3 v&otilde;i 4 s&auml;testatu rikkumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>4) less than two years have passed since the revocation of an explosive substances sales permit previously issued to the applicant, and the revocation of the sales permit arose from a violation of the provisions of clauses 15 (1) 2), 3) or 4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;giloa kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of explosive substances sales permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;giloa v&otilde;ib kehtetuks tunnistada, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An explosive substances sales permit may be revoked if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) m&uuml;&uuml;giloa omanik ei ole alustanud tegevust 12 kuu jooksul loa v&auml;ljaandmise p&auml;evast arvates; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the holder of the sales permit has not commenced activities within twelve months after the date of issue of the permit; </inglise>
<eesti>2) m&uuml;&uuml;giloa taotlemisel on teadvalt esitatud valeandmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) false information is knowingly provided upon application for the sales permit; </inglise>
<eesti>3) on sooritatud tehing, mis v&auml;ljub m&uuml;&uuml;giloaga lubatud tegevuse raamest; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a transaction is concluded which is beyond the scope of activity permitted by the sales permit; </inglise>
<eesti>4) m&uuml;&uuml;giloa omanik on rikkunud k&auml;esolevat seadust v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktides kehtestatud korda. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the holder of the sales permit violates this Act or any procedure established by legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 loetletud m&uuml;&uuml;giloa kehtetuks tunnistamise aluste ilmnemisel v&otilde;ib Politseiamet teha ettekirjutusi rikkumiste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks ja peatada m&uuml;&uuml;giloa kehtivuse kuni rikkumise k&otilde;rvaldamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If grounds for the revocation of an explosive substances sales permit set out in subsection (1) of this section become evident, the Police Administration may issue precepts for the elimination of violations and suspend the sales permit until the violations are eliminated. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali soetusluba </eesti>
<inglise>Explosive substances procurement permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali soetusluba annab sellel n&auml;idatud f&uuml;&uuml;silisele v&otilde;i juriidilisele isikule &otilde;iguse loal m&auml;rgitud l&otilde;hkematerjali soetamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An explosive substances procurement permit grants the natural or legal person indicated therein the right to procure the explosive substances set out in the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali soetusloa v&auml;ljaandmise aluseks on l&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;giluba, l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise v&otilde;i l&otilde;hkematerjaliga t&ouml;&ouml;tamise luba v&otilde;i muu dokument, mis t&otilde;endab l&otilde;hkematerjali vajadust ja l&otilde;hkematerjali kasutamise p&otilde;hjendatust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The issue of an explosive substances procurement permit is based on an explosive substances sales permit, permit for blasting operations, permit for work with explosive substances or other document which provides certification of the need for explosive substances and justification for the use thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 65, 377) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 65, 377) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkematerjali soetusloa v&auml;ljastab l&otilde;hkematerjali kasutava isiku v&otilde;i asutuse asukohaj&auml;rgne politseiprefektuur. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An explosive substances procurement permit is issued by the Police Prefecture of the location of the person or agency which uses the explosive substance. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;hkematerjali soetusloas n&auml;idatakse l&otilde;hkematerjali soetaja nimi ja aadress, soetatava l&otilde;hkematerjali nimetus, kogus ja klassifikatsiooni kood, l&otilde;hkematerjalilao aadress, soetusloa v&auml;ljaandja ees- ja perekonnanimi, ametikoht, v&auml;ljaandmise kuup&auml;ev ja kehtivuse aeg. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The name and address of the procurer of an explosive substance, the name, quantity and classification code of the explosive substance to be procured, the address of the explosive substances store, the given name, surname and office of the issuer of the permit, and the date of issue and term of the permit are indicated in an explosive substances procurement permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) L&otilde;hkematerjali soetusluba antakse v&auml;lja kehtivusega kuni &uuml;ks aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An explosive substances procurement permit is issued for a term of up to one year. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;juvatel p&otilde;hjustel on loa v&auml;ljaandjal &otilde;igus pikendada loa kestvust kuni kolme kuu v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>The issuer of a permit has the right with good reason to extend the permit for up to three months. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) L&otilde;hkematerjali soetusloa h&auml;vimisest v&otilde;i kaotsiminekust on loa omanik kohustatud viivitamatult teatama loa v&auml;ljastanud v&otilde;i oma asukohaj&auml;rgsele politseiprefektuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Upon the destruction or loss of an explosive substances procurement permit, the holder of the permit is obliged to notify promptly the Police Prefecture which issued the permit or the Police Prefecture of the location of the holder. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali soetusloa kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of explosive substances procurement permit </inglise>
<eesti>Soetusloa v&auml;ljaandnud politseiprefektuur v&otilde;i Politseiamet tunnistab soetusloa kehtetuks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>The Police Prefecture which issues a procurement permit or the Police Administration shall revoke the permit if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) seda taotleb loa omanik; </eesti>
<inglise>1) so requested by the holder of the permit; </inglise>
<eesti>2) soetusloa taotlemisel on teadvalt esitatud valeandmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) false information is knowingly provided upon application for the procurement permit; </inglise>
<eesti>3) juriidilise isiku tegevus on l&otilde;ppenud v&otilde;i asutus on likvideeritud; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the activities of the legal person are terminated or the agency is liquidated; </inglise>
<eesti>4) loa omanik on surnud, surnuks v&otilde;i teadmata kadunuks tunnistatud; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the holder of the permit dies or is declared dead or missing; </inglise>
<eesti>5) loa omanik on l&otilde;hkematerjali soetamisel rikkunud k&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusakti s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>5) upon procurement of explosive substances, the holder of the permit violates the provisions of this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;k </eesti>
<inglise>Sale of explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali v&otilde;ib m&uuml;&uuml;a ainult l&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;giluba omav isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Only a holder of an explosive substances sales permit may sell explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) M&uuml;&uuml;a v&otilde;ib ainult sellist l&otilde;hkematerjali, mille kohta on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 3 s&auml;testatu kohane l&otilde;hkematerjali alaline kasutusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) It is only permitted to sell explosive substances concerning which a permanent explosive substances permit of use as provided for in &sect; 3 of this Act exists. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;ja peab l&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;gil j&auml;rgima j&auml;rgmisi n&otilde;udeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon the sale of explosive substances, a seller of explosive substances shall adhere to the following requirements: </inglise>
<eesti>1) m&uuml;&uuml;ma l&otilde;hkematerjali vaid l&otilde;hkematerjali soetusluba omavale isikule; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to sell explosive substances only to holders of explosive substances procurement permits; </inglise>
<eesti>2) hoidma m&uuml;&uuml;giks etten&auml;htud l&otilde;hkematerjali vaid kohas ja tingimustes, mis vastavad k&auml;esoleva seadusega v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to store explosive substances intended for sale only in locations and under conditions which comply with the requirements of this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof: </inglise>
<eesti>3) pidama arvestust m&uuml;&uuml;dava l&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;ibe &uuml;le ja kindlustama n&otilde;utava dokumentatsiooni s&auml;ilimise vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 27 s&auml;testatule; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to keep records of the sales of explosive substances and ensure the preservation of required documentation pursuant to the provisions of &sect; 27 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kaasa andma l&otilde;hkematerjali soetajale l&otilde;hkematerjali eestikeelse kasutusjuhendi. </eesti>
<inglise>4) to provide procurers of explosive substances with an explosive substance user manual in Estonian. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Keelatud on teadvalt m&uuml;&uuml;a defektset l&otilde;hkematerjali. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) It is prohibited to knowingly sell defective explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>Defektne l&otilde;hkematerjal antakse &uuml;le h&auml;vitamiseks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 45 l&otilde;ikes 2 n&auml;idatud asutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>Defective explosive substances shall be transferred to the agency designated in subsection 45 (2) of this Act for destruction. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 3 punktid 1 ja 3 ei kehti I ja II klassi p&uuml;rotehniliste toodete jaem&uuml;&uuml;gil. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Clauses (3) 1) and 3) of this section do not apply to the retail trade of pyrotechnic articles of divisions I and II. </inglise>
<eesti>(5 (1)) Alla 14-aastastele isikutele on p&uuml;rotehniliste toodete m&uuml;&uuml;k keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(5 (1)) The sale of pyrotechnic articles to persons under 14 years of age is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud m&uuml;&uuml;gipiirang ei kehti nende I klassi p&uuml;rotehniliste toodete suhtes, mille kasutusloas on alla 14-aastastele isikutele m&uuml;&uuml;ki lubav m&auml;rge. </eesti>
<inglise>Such restriction on sale does not extend to pyrotechnic articles of division I concerning which an explosive substances permit has been issued which indicates that the sale of such article is permitted to persons under 14 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>14-18-aastastele isikutele on lubatud m&uuml;&uuml;a ainult I klassi p&uuml;rotehnilisi tooteid. </eesti>
<inglise>Only pyrotechnic articles of division I may be sold to persons who are between 14 to 18 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.10.2001 entered into force 01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </inglise>
<eesti>(5 (2)) Paugutite jaem&uuml;&uuml;k on keelatud alates 1. novembrist kuni 30. detsembrini (kaasa arvatud). </eesti>
<inglise>(5 (2)) The retail trade of crackers is prohibited from 1 November to 30 December (inclusive). </inglise>
<eesti>Paugutite jaem&uuml;&uuml;giks loetakse paugutite m&uuml;&uuml;giks pakkumist v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;ki tarbijale tarbijakaitseseaduse (RT I 1994, 2, 13; RT I 1999, 35, 450; 102, 907; 2000, 40, 252; 59, 379; 2001, 50, 283 ja 289; 56, 332) &sect; 3 punkti 1 t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise>The retail trade of crackers is deemed to be the sale or offer for sale thereof to consumers within the meaning of clause 3 1) of the Consumer Protection Act (RT I 1994, 2, 13; RT I 1999, 35, 450; 102, 907; 2000, 40, 252; 59, 379; 2001, 50, 283 and 289; 56, 332). </inglise>
<eesti>(10.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.10.2001 entered into force 01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Isik, kel puudub tegevusluba tema seaduslikus valduses oleva l&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;giks, v&otilde;ib seda teha vastavat luba omava &auml;ri&uuml;hingu kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A person who does not hold an activity licence for the sale of explosive substances in the lawful possession of such person may sell such explosive substances through a commercial undertaking which holds an appropriate permit. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali sisse- ja v&auml;ljavedu ning transiit </eesti>
<inglise>Import, export and transit of explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali sisse- ja v&auml;ljavedu ning l&auml;biv transiit toimub k&auml;esoleva seaduse, tolliseadustiku ning strateegilise kauba sisse- ja v&auml;ljaveo ning transiidi seadusega (RT I 1999, 57, 597) ja nende alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud korras, samuti Eesti Vabariigile kohustuslike rahvusvaheliste kokkulepete ning Eesti Vabariigi ja teise riigi vahel s&otilde;lmitud kokkuleppe alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The import, export and through transit of explosive substances shall be carried out pursuant to the procedure established by this Act, the Customs Code, the Strategic Goods Import, Export and Transit Act (RT I 1994, 30, 466) and legislation issued on the basis thereof, and on the basis of international agreements binding on the Republic of Estonia and of bilateral agreements between the Republic of Estonia and other states. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali sissevedu Eestisse ja l&otilde;hkematerjali, mis ei ole kantud strateegiliste kaupade nimekirja, v&auml;ljavedu Eestist toimub Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni poolt v&auml;ljastatud &uuml;hekordse sisse- v&otilde;i v&auml;ljaveo loa alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The import of explosive substances into Estonia and the export from Estonia of explosive substances which are not entered in the list of strategic goods shall be carried out on the basis of a single import or export permit issued by the Technical Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali sisseveoloa avaldus tuleb koosk&otilde;lastada l&otilde;hkematerjali soetusloa v&auml;ljaandnud politseiprefektuuriga v&otilde;i lisada avaldusele soetusloa &auml;rakiri. </eesti>
<inglise>An application for an explosive substances import permit shall be concorded with the Police Prefecture which issued the explosive substances procurement permit, or a copy of the procurement permit shall be appended to the application. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkematerjali sisse- ja v&auml;ljavedu v&otilde;ivad teostada isikud ning asutused, kellel on l&otilde;hkematerjali sisse- v&otilde;i v&auml;ljaveo luba. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The import or export of explosive substances may be conducted by persons and agencies which hold an explosive substances import or export permit respectively. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;hkematerjali v&auml;ljaveoloa taotlusele tuleb lisada sissevedaja asukohaj&auml;rgse riigi f&uuml;&uuml;silisele v&otilde;i juriidilisele isikule v&auml;ljastatud l&otilde;hkematerjali soetusluba ja selle eesti- v&otilde;i ingliskeelne t&otilde;lge. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An explosive substances procurement permit issued to a natural or legal person of the country of the location of the importer and a translation of the procurement permit into Estonian or English shall be appended to an application for an explosive substances export permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Sisse v&otilde;ib vedada ainult sellist l&otilde;hkematerjali, millel on kasutusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) It is only permitted to import explosive substances concerning which an explosive substances permit of use has been issued. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali hoidmine ja arvestus </eesti>
<inglise>Storage and Recording of Explosive Substances </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali hoidmise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for storage of explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali tuleb hoida tingimustes, mis tagavad selle s&auml;ilimise ja ohutuse &uuml;mbrusele ning v&auml;listavad l&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;ttesaadavuse k&otilde;rvalistele isikutele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Explosive substances shall be stored under conditions which ensure their preservation and safety to the surroundings and which preclude access by unauthorised persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali v&otilde;ib alaliselt hoida l&otilde;hkematerjalilaos, konteineris v&otilde;i seifis. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Explosive substances may be stored permanently in explosive substances stores, containers or safes. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on l&otilde;hkematerjaliladu &uuml;ks v&otilde;i mitu l&otilde;hkematerjalihoidlat koos abiehitistega, mis paiknevad &uuml;hisel taraga piiratud territooriumil, allmaalao puhul aga l&otilde;hkematerjali hoiuruumid, ni&scaron;id ja abiruumid koos lattu viivate kaeve&otilde;&otilde;ntega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) For the purposes of this Act, an explosive substances store is one or several explosive substances magazines together with auxiliary structures which are located on a common territory surrounded by a fence, or in the case of an underground store, storage space, pockets and auxiliary space with excavated sections which lead to the store. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Pealmaa l&otilde;hkematerjaliladu peavad valvama relvastatud valvurid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A surface explosive substances store shall be guarded by armed guards. </inglise>
<eesti>Lao valvere&zcaron;iimi ja vajaliku valvurite arvu m&auml;&auml;rab lao omanik koosk&otilde;lastatult asukohaj&auml;rgse politseiprefektuuriga igal konkreetsel juhul eraldi. </eesti>
<inglise>The security regime for the store and the necessary number of guards shall be determined by the owner of the store in concordance with the local Police Prefecture separately for each specific case. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) P&uuml;rotehniliste toodete ladu v&otilde;i ruum, kus asub l&otilde;hkematerjali seif, peab olema valvesignalisatsiooniga. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Stores for pyrotechnic articles or spaces where a safe for explosive substances is located shall be equipped with a security alarm system. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjaliladu </eesti>
<inglise>Explosive substances stores </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjalilaod jaotatakse kasutusaja j&auml;rgi alalisteks ja ajutisteks l&otilde;hkematerjaliladudeks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Explosive substances stores are divided into permanent and temporary explosive substances stores according to the duration of use of the stores. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Alalise l&otilde;hkematerjalilao kasutusaeg on &uuml;le kolme aasta ja ajutise l&otilde;hkematerjalilao kasutusaeg on kuni kolm aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The duration of use of permanent explosive substances stores is more than three years and the duration of use of temporary explosive substances stores is up to three years. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkematerjaliladude ehitamine: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Construction of explosive substances stores: </inglise>
<eesti>1) pealmaa l&otilde;hkematerjaliladu ehitatakse planeerimis- ja ehitusseadusega s&auml;testatud alustel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) surface explosive substances stores shall be constructed on the bases provided for in the Planning and Building Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) allmaa l&otilde;hkematerjaliladu ehitatakse maap&otilde;ueseadusega (RT I 1994, 86/87, 1488; 1995, 75, 1321; 1996, 49, 953; 1997, 52, 833; 86, 1461; 93, 1562; 1998, 64/65, 1005; 1999, 10, 155; 54, 583; 95, 843; 2000, 54, 348; 102, 670) s&auml;testatud alustel. </eesti>
<inglise>2) underground explosive substances stores shall be constructed on the bases provided for in the Earth's Crust Act (RT I 1994, 86/87, 1488; 1995, 75, 1321; 1996, 49, 953; 1997, 52, 833; 86, 1461; 93, 1562; 1998, 64/65, 1005; 1999, 10, 155; 54, 583; 95, 843; 2000, 54, 348; 102, 670). </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;hkematerjalilao asukoht peab olema selline, et v&otilde;imaliku avarii korral laos oleks tagatud l&auml;hedalasuvate inimeste ohutus, nende vara s&auml;ilimine ning minimaalne keskkonnakahjustus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The site of an explosive substances store shall be such that, in the case of an accident in the store, the safety of people in the vicinity, the preservation of their property and minimal environmental damage are ensured. </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;imalikke keskkonnakahjustusi hinnatakse l&otilde;hkematerjalilao asukoha valikul keskkonnaekspertiisiga. </eesti>
<inglise>Potential environmental damage is assessed upon the choice of a site for an explosive substances store by an environmental impact assessment. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Liikuv l&otilde;hkematerjaliladu </eesti>
<inglise>Mobile explosive substances store </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liikuv l&otilde;hkematerjaliladu v&otilde;ib olla nii l&otilde;hkematerjali kasutajal kui ka l&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;jal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Users and sellers of explosive substances may have mobile explosive substances stores. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Liikuv l&otilde;hkematerjaliladu v&otilde;ib paikneda autol v&otilde;i haagisel, mille veoseruum peab olema kinnine ja pragudeta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A mobile explosive substances store may be situated in a vehicle or trailer, the cargo space of which shall be enclosed and without cracks. </inglise>
<eesti>Veoseruumi konstruktsioon peab olema rasks&uuml;ttivatest materjalidest ja piisavalt kaitsma veetavaid veoseid. </eesti>
<inglise>The load-bearing part of the cargo space shall be constructed from non-flammable materials and shall provide adequate protection to loads carried. </inglise>
<eesti>Veoseruumi vooderdusmaterjalina ei ole lubatud kasutada s&auml;demeidtekitavaid materjale. </eesti>
<inglise>The use of spark-generating materials as lining material for cargo spaces is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>Veoseruumi isolatsioon ja soojuslikud omadused peavad olema v&auml;hemalt samav&auml;&auml;rsed 10 cm paksuse rasks&uuml;ttiva puidu kihiga kaetud metallv&auml;lisseina omadustega ning selles v&otilde;ib hoida ja vedada l&otilde;hkematerjali kuni poole auto v&otilde;i haagise kandev&otilde;ime ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>The isolation and thermal characteristics of the cargo space shall be not less than equivalent to the characteristics of a metal external wall covered with a layer of non-flammable timber with a thickness of 10 centimetres, and explosive substances up to one half of the load-bearing capacity of the vehicle or trailer may be stored and carried in such cargo space. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Erinevate sobivusr&uuml;hmade l&otilde;hkematerjale hoitakse kinnise veoseruumi eraldi ustega osades (hoiuruumides), kusjuures B sobivusgrupi l&otilde;hkematerjali hoiuruum peab paiknema veoseruumi esiosas ja selle sisek&uuml;lgedel peab olema niisuguse tugevusega metallekraan, mis v&auml;listab detonatsiooni edasiandmise teistele veoseruumis olevatele l&otilde;hkematerjalidele ja tagab kabiinisolijate ohutuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Explosive substances of different compatibility groups shall be stored in parts of a closed cargo space fitted with separate doors (storage spaces); the storage space for explosive substances of compatibility group B shall be situated at the front of the cargo space, and the internal surface of such storage space shall be covered with a metal screen of a sturdiness which precludes the transfer of detonation to other explosive substances within the cargo space and ensures the safety of persons in the driver's cab. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Liikuva l&otilde;hkematerjalilao hoiuruumide uksed peavad olema lukustatud sise- ja ripplukuga selliselt, et rippluku p&otilde;&otilde;n katab siseluku v&otilde;tmeava. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The doors of storage spaces of a mobile explosive substances store shall be locked with an inner lock and a padlock in such a manner that the bow of the padlock covers the keyhole of the inner lock. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Liikuva l&otilde;hkematerjalilao asukoha all m&otilde;istetakse l&otilde;hkematerjaliga auto v&otilde;i haagise alalist seisukohta, mis peab vastama k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 21 l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatule ja l&otilde;hkematerjalilao valve peab vastama k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 20 l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The site of a mobile explosive substances store is defined as the permanent site of a vehicle or trailer which contains explosive substances; such site shall comply with the provisions of subsection 21 (4) of this Act, and the security measures implemented for an explosive substances store shall comply with the provisions of subsection 20 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali hoiuluba </eesti>
<inglise>Explosive substances storage permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjaliladu ei tohi kasutusele v&otilde;tta enne, kui komisjon on seda kontrollinud ja kasutusk&otilde;lblikuks tunnistanud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An explosive substances store shall not be used before the committee has inspected the store and declared it fit for use. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Komisjoni kokkukutsujaks on Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon ja tema esindaja on &uuml;htlasi komisjoni esimees. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The committee shall be convened by the Technical Inspectorate, and the representative of the Technical Inspectorate shall be the chairman of the committee. </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjoni t&ouml;&ouml;st v&otilde;tavad koosk&otilde;lastatult osa lao asukohaj&auml;rgse T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni, politseiprefektuuri ja tulet&otilde;rjej&auml;relevalve (allmaa l&otilde;hkematerjalilao puhul m&auml;ep&auml;&auml;ste) esindajad. </eesti>
<inglise>The Labour Inspectorate, Police Prefecture and fire fighting supervisory body (in the case of an underground explosive substances store, the mine rescue service) of the location of the store shall each appoint a representative to participate in the work of the committee and each appointment shall be approved by the other bodies. </inglise>
<eesti>Lao omanik v&otilde;i valdaja esitab komisjonile l&otilde;hkematerjalilao passi kolmes eksemplaris. </eesti>
<inglise>The owner or possessor of the store shall submit three original copies of the documentation concerning the explosive substances store to the committee. </inglise>
<eesti>Pass peab sisaldama lao aadressi, lao asukoha plaani m&otilde;&otilde;tkavas kuni 1: 50000, lao plaani m&otilde;&otilde;tkavas 1: 1000, lao k&otilde;igi ehitiste plaane m&otilde;&otilde;tkavas 1: 100, k&otilde;igi hoidlate mahutavust, lao &uuml;ldmahutavust ja laojuhataja telefoninumbrit. </eesti>
<inglise>The documentation shall set out the address of the store, a plan of the site of the store on a scale of up to 1: 50000, a plan of the store on a scale of 1: 1000, plans of all structures of the store on a scale of 1: 100, the capacity of all magazines, the total capacity of the store and the telephone number of the head of the store. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui kontrolli tulemusena on l&otilde;hkematerjaliladu tunnistatud kasutamisk&otilde;lblikuks, annab Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon l&otilde;hkematerjali hoiuloa. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an explosive substances store is declared to be fit for use as the result of an inspection, the Technical Inspectorate shall issue an explosive substances storage permit. </inglise>
<eesti>Hoiuloa &auml;rakirjad saadetakse komisjoni liikmetele kahe n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates loa v&auml;ljaandmise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>Copies of the storage permit shall be sent to the members of the committee within two weeks after the date of issue of the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>Hoiuluba antakse alalise l&otilde;hkematerjalilao valdajale t&auml;htajaga kuni kolm aastat ja ajutise l&otilde;hkematerjalilao valdajale t&auml;htajaga kuni &uuml;ks aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>A storage permit is issued to the possessor of a permanent explosive substances store for a term of up to three years and to the possessor of a temporary explosive substances store for a term of up to one year. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;hkematerjali hoiuloaga m&auml;&auml;ratakse laos hoitava l&otilde;hkematerjali maksimaalne kogus allklasside ja sobivusr&uuml;hmade j&auml;rgi, samuti hoidmise t&auml;htaeg. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The maximum quantity of explosive substances which may be stored in an explosive substances store and the term of storage are determined according to subdivision and compatibility group in the explosive substances storage permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Alalise l&otilde;hkematerjalilao hoiuloa kehtivust v&otilde;ib pikendada kuni kolme aasta ja ajutise l&otilde;hkematerjalilao hoiuloa kehtivust kuni &uuml;he aasta v&otilde;rra p&auml;rast lao seisukorra kontrollimist k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud komisjoni liikmete poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A storage permit for a permanent explosive substances store may be extended for up to three years and a storage permit for a temporary explosive substances store may be extended for up to one year following inspection of the condition of the store by the members of the committee specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Asutus v&otilde;i isik, kellel on l&otilde;hkematerjaliga t&ouml;&ouml;tamise luba, v&otilde;ib ilma hoiuloata hoida kuni 5 kg l&otilde;hkematerjali seifis, mis paikneb mitteeluruumis, on tugevalt kinnitatud seina v&otilde;i p&otilde;randa k&uuml;lge ja mille tulekindlus on v&auml;hemalt 0,75 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An agency or person who holds a permit for work with explosive substances may, without a storage permit, store up to 5 kilograms of explosive substances in a safe which is situated in a non-residential space, which is firmly fixed to a wall or the floor, and which shall be flameproof for not less than 0.75 hours. </inglise>
<eesti>Ruum peab olema valvesignalisatsiooniga, seif asuma k&uuml;ttekehast v&auml;hemalt &uuml;he meetri kaugusel ja seifi l&auml;hedal olema &uuml;ks k&auml;situlekustuti minimaalse mahuga 6 kg kuiva pulbrit (v&otilde;i samav&auml;&auml;rses koguses kustutusainet). </eesti>
<inglise>The space shall be equipped with a security alarm system, the safe shall be located at a distance of at least 1 metre from any heating element, and one portable fire extinguisher with a minimum capacity of 6 kilograms of dry powder (or an equivalent amount of extinguishing agent) shall be situated near the safe. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) (Kehtetu - 13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 65, 377) </eesti>
<inglise>(7) (Repealed -13,060, 2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 65, 377) </inglise>
<eesti>(8) L&otilde;hkematerjali hoidmise kord kaevanduse, karj&auml;&auml;ri v&otilde;i kollektori allmaakonteinerites kehtestatakse ettev&otilde;tte juhendiga koosk&otilde;lastatult Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooniga. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The procedure for storage of explosive substances in underground containers in mines, open cast mines or sewers shall be established in the written policies of an enterprise in concordance with the Technical Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Hulgim&uuml;&uuml;giks ja keskmise ning suurilutulestiku tegemiseks etten&auml;htud p&uuml;rotehniliste toodete hoidmiseks taotletakse hoiuluba vastavalt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1, 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) Storage permits for the storage of pyrotechnic articles prescribed for wholesale trade and for medium and large fireworks shall be applied for pursuant to the provisions of subsections (1), (2) and (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali hoidmine l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise kohal </eesti>
<inglise>Storage of explosive substances at blasting site </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise kohal v&otilde;ib l&otilde;hkematerjali hoida l&otilde;hkaja v&otilde;i abit&ouml;&ouml;lise j&auml;relevalve all &uuml;he vahetuse vajaduse ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The amount of explosive substances needed by one shift may be stored at a blasting site under the supervision of a blaster or support staff. </inglise>
<eesti>Seejuures peavad detonaatorid ja detonatsioonireleed olema eraldi kastides v&otilde;i kassettides. </eesti>
<inglise>Detonators and detonating relays shall be stored in separate boxes or cassettes. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjal peab olema muudest t&ouml;&ouml;kohtadest v&auml;hemalt 20 m kaugusel. </eesti>
<inglise>Explosive substances shall be stored not less than 20 metres from other jobsites. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; l&otilde;hkematerjaliga tehtav t&ouml;&ouml;, mis h&otilde;lmab looduslike materjalide (kivimite, puidu, j&auml;&auml; jt.) ja tehismaterjalide (betooni, kivi- ja tellism&uuml;&uuml;ritise, metallide jt.) kontrollitavat purustamist ning teisaldamist, samuti nende struktuuri v&otilde;i vormi muutmist plahvatuse abil, seismilise laine tekitamist maap&otilde;ues ja ebakvaliteetse l&otilde;hkematerjali h&auml;vitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, blasting is work performed with explosive substances which includes the controlled destruction and removal of natural materials (rock, timber, ice, etc.) and synthetic materials (concrete, stone and brick masonry, metal, etc.), and the alteration of their structure or form by blasting, the creation of seismic waves in the earth and the destruction of substandard explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui l&otilde;hkeaukude laadimine kestab kauem kui &uuml;ks vahetus, v&otilde;ib kogu l&otilde;hkamiseks vajaliku l&otilde;hkematerjali hoida t&ouml;&ouml;kohal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the charging of blast holes continues for longer than the duration of one shift, all explosive substances needed for blasting may be stored at the jobsite. </inglise>
<eesti>Detonaatorid ja detonatsioonireleed peavad olema l&otilde;hkeainest eraldi ja asuma v&auml;ljaspool laadimistsooni. </eesti>
<inglise>Detonators and detonating relays shall be stored separately from explosives and located outside the charging zone. </inglise>
<eesti>Laadimistsooni all m&otilde;istetakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses l&otilde;hkeaukude ja sellega piirnevat v&auml;hemalt 20 m laiust ala, mille m&auml;&auml;rab l&otilde;hket&ouml;id juhtiv isik. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this Act, a charging zone is defined as an area where blast holes are located together with an area of not less than 20 metres in width bordering thereon, and such areas shall be determined by the person in charge of blasting. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;d tehakse &uuml;he ohtliku ala piirides eri kohtades, peab seal hoitav l&otilde;hkematerjal olema kaitstud kildude eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If blasting is conducted in different locations within the boundaries of one danger zone, explosive substances stored within such danger zone shall be protected from flyrock. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali vastuv&otilde;tmine ja v&auml;ljastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Receipt and issue of explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjal v&otilde;etakse laos arvele tarnija saatekirja alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Explosive substances shall be registered in a store on the basis of a way-bill from the supplier. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;ks v&auml;ljastatud, kuid seal kulutamata j&auml;&auml;nud ja lattu tagastatud l&otilde;hkematerjal v&otilde;etakse arvele t&ouml;&ouml;k&auml;su alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>Explosive substances which are issued for blasting but which are not used and are returned to the store shall be registered on the basis of a work order. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali saatekirja kirjutab l&otilde;hkematerjali tarnija v&auml;lja tellimiskirja ja l&otilde;hkematerjali soetusloa alusel kolmes eksemplaris, millest &uuml;ks j&auml;&auml;b tarnijale, teine ja kolmas antakse l&otilde;hkematerjali soetajale l&otilde;hkematerjali arvelev&otilde;tmiseks laos ja arveldamiseks raamatupidamises. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A supplier of explosive substances shall prepare an explosive substance way-bill on the basis of a written order and an explosive substances procurement permit, in three original copies, one of which shall be kept by the supplier, and the second and third original copies of which shall be given to the procurer of the explosive substance for registration of the explosive substance in a store and for accounting purposes. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkematerjali saatekirja v&otilde;ib kasutada ka ettev&otilde;ttesiseselt, kui l&otilde;hkematerjali ei vii l&otilde;hkematerjalilaost t&ouml;&ouml;kohta l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;d teostav l&otilde;hkaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An explosive substance way-bill may be used internally as long as the explosive substance is not taken from an explosive substances store to a jobsite by the blaster conducting the blasting. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;hkematerjali saatekiri peab sisaldama k&otilde;iki ohtlike ainete veon&otilde;uetes etten&auml;htud andmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An explosive substance way-bill shall contain all information prescribed by the carriage requirements for hazardous substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;k&auml;sk on dokument, mille kirjutab v&auml;lja l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;de tegemise eest vastutav isik v&otilde;i l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;de j&auml;relevalve eest vastutav isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A work order is a document which is signed by the person responsible for blasting or the person responsible for supervision over blasting. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjal v&auml;ljastatakse l&otilde;hkajale t&ouml;&ouml;k&auml;su alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>Explosive substances shall be issued to blasters on the basis of a work order. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;k&auml;sk peab sisaldama j&auml;rgmisi andmeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A work order shall set out the following information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vastutava l&otilde;hkaja nimi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name of the blaster responsible for blasting; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teiste, vastutava l&otilde;hkaja alluvuses t&ouml;&ouml;tavate l&otilde;hkajate nimed; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the names of other blasters subordinate to the blaster responsible for blasting; </inglise>
<eesti>3) l&otilde;hkamise kuup&auml;ev ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the date and place of blasting; </inglise>
<eesti>4) l&otilde;hatavate laengute arv, laengute suurused, kasutatavad l&otilde;hkamisvahendid, nende hulk ja l&otilde;hkematerjali &uuml;ldkogus. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the number of blasted charges, the masses of the charges, the means of blasting used, the amount thereof and the total amount of explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali vastuv&otilde;tmise ja v&auml;ljastamise peatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension of receipt and issue of explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui l&otilde;hkematerjalilaos, konteineris v&otilde;i seifis avastatakse l&otilde;hkematerjali puuduj&auml;&auml;k v&otilde;i &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;k, tuleb l&otilde;hkematerjali vastuv&otilde;tmine ja v&auml;ljastamine kohe peatada ja viia l&auml;bi ametkondlik juurdlus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a deficit or surplus of explosive substances is detected in an explosive substances store, container or safe, the receipt and issue of explosive substances shall be immediately suspended and a departmental investigation shall be conducted. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui juurdluse k&auml;igus ei &otilde;nnestu l&otilde;hkematerjali puuduj&auml;&auml;gi v&otilde;i &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;gi p&otilde;hjust tuvastada v&otilde;i on selle p&otilde;hjuseks mingi ebaseaduslik toiming, peab l&otilde;hkematerjali omanik v&otilde;i valdaja tegutsema vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 51 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>If the reason for the deficit or surplus of explosive substances cannot be established in the course of the investigation, or if the reason for such deficit or surplus is an unlawful act, the owner or possessor of the explosive substances shall act pursuant to the provisions of subsection 51 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali vastuv&otilde;tmist ja v&auml;ljastamist v&otilde;ib j&auml;tkata, kui on v&auml;lja selgitatud l&otilde;hkematerjali puuduj&auml;&auml;gi v&otilde;i &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;gi p&otilde;hjus ja rakendatud abin&otilde;ud analoogse juhtumi &auml;rahoidmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The receipt and issue of explosive substances may be resumed if the reason for the deficit or surplus is established and measures for the prevention of similar incidents are applied. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali arvestus </eesti>
<inglise>Records of explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjalitehase v&otilde;i l&otilde;hkeaine valmistamispunkti omanik v&otilde;i valdaja peab pidama valmistatava l&otilde;hkematerjali igap&auml;evast arvestust koguste ja liikide j&auml;rgi vormikohases arvestusraamatus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Owners and possessors of explosive substances plants and places of manufacture of explosives shall keep daily records of manufactured explosive substances by quantity and type in ledgers in prescribed form. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjalitehase omanik v&otilde;i valdaja peab pidama vormikohast arvestusraamatut ka l&otilde;hkematerjali tootmistehnoloogias etten&auml;htud katsete, nendel kasutatud l&otilde;hkematerjali koguse ja katsetulemuste &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Owners and possessors of explosive substances plants shall also keep ledgers in prescribed form concerning tests required due to the production technology used in the production of explosive substances, the quantity of explosive substances used therein and the test results. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkematerjalilaos peetakse l&otilde;hkematerjali arvestust arvutis v&otilde;i kahe arvestusraamatu abil: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Records of explosive substances in an explosive substances store shall be kept on computer or with the aid of two ledgers: </inglise>
<eesti>1) l&otilde;hkematerjali sissetuleku ja v&auml;ljamineku raamat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the ledger of explosive substances received in and issued from the store; </inglise>
<eesti>2) l&otilde;hkematerjali kulu raamat. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the ledger of explosive substances used. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Arvestusraamatu lehed peavad olema nummerdatud, n&ouml;&ouml;ritud ja kinnitatud Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni pitseriga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The pages of a ledger shall be numbered, bound with string and sealed with the seal of the Technical Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) L&otilde;hkematerjali sissetuleku ja v&auml;ljamineku raamatus m&auml;rgitakse l&otilde;hkematerjalilattu sissetulnud ja sealt v&auml;ljastatud l&otilde;hkematerjal. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Explosive substances received in and issued from an explosive substances store shall be set out in the ledger of explosive substances received in and issued from the store. </inglise>
<eesti>Iga l&otilde;hkematerjali ja selle iga liigi kohta peetakse eraldi arvestust ning selleks eraldatakse raamatus iga liigi kohta vastav arv lehti. </eesti>
<inglise>A separate record shall be kept concerning each explosive substance and each type of explosive substance, and a corresponding number of pages of the ledger shall be allocated to each type of explosive substance. </inglise>
<eesti>Raamatus kajastub igap&auml;evane laoseis. </eesti>
<inglise>The daily inventory shall be stated in the ledger. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) L&otilde;hkematerjali kulu raamatusse m&auml;rgitakse t&ouml;&ouml;k&auml;su alusel v&auml;ljastatud l&otilde;hkematerjal, samuti v&otilde;etakse uuesti arvele t&ouml;&ouml;k&auml;su alusel v&auml;ljastatud, kuid kulutamata j&auml;&auml;nud ja tagastatud l&otilde;hkematerjal. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Explosive substances issued from a store on the basis of a work order shall be set out in the ledger of explosive substances used, and explosive substances issued on the basis of a work order but which are not used and returned shall be re-registered in such ledger. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Iga t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva l&otilde;pus kantakse l&otilde;hkematerjali kulu raamatus kuluna arvestatud l&otilde;hkematerjal l&otilde;hkematerjali sissetuleku ja v&auml;ljamineku raamatus sama p&auml;eva v&auml;ljaminekuna maha. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Explosive substances registered as used in the ledger of explosive substances used shall be written off in the ledger of explosive substances received in and issued from the store at the end of each working day as having been issued on the same day. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis loetletud arvestusraamatuid tuleb s&auml;ilitada viis aastat, arvates viimase sissekande tegemise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The ledgers listed in this section shall be preserved for five years from the date of the last entry. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali arvestus arvutis </eesti>
<inglise>Recording of explosive substances on computer </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali arvestust v&otilde;ib pidada arvutis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Records of explosive substances may be maintained on computer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui l&otilde;hkematerjali arvestust peetakse arvutis, tuleb kehtivad kanded s&auml;ilitada v&auml;ljatr&uuml;kkidena. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If records of explosive substances are maintained on computer, valid entries shall be stored as printouts. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkematerjali arvestuse kanne arvutis loetakse tehtuks, kui see on salvestatud l&otilde;hkematerjali arvestuse kannetele m&auml;&auml;ratud andmebaasi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An entry of a record of an explosive substance on computer is deemed to be completed when the entry is stored in the database designated for entries of records of explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;hkematerjali arvestus arvutis peab vastama arvestusraamatutega etten&auml;htule </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The recording of explosive substances on computer shall comply with the requirements prescribed for ledgers. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemise ja k&auml;ibe eest vastutavad isikud ning nende atesteerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Persons Responsible for Handling of and Trade in Explosive Substances and Evaluation of Such Persons </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemise ja k&auml;ibe eest vastutavad isikud </eesti>
<inglise>Persons responsible for handling of and trade in explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemise ja k&auml;ibe eest vastutavaks isikuks v&otilde;i tema asendajaks v&otilde;ib olla v&auml;hemalt 21-aastane Eesti kodanik, samuti alalise v&otilde;i t&auml;htajalise elamisloa alusel Eestis viibiv v&auml;lismaalane. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Estonian citizens who have attained twenty-one years of age or aliens residing in Estonia on the basis of a permanent or temporary residence permit may operate as persons responsible for the handling of and trade in explosive substances or as substitutes for such persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act: </inglise>
<eesti>1) l&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemine - l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamine, t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine, &uuml;mbert&ouml;&ouml;tlemine, taastamine, pakendamine, komplekteerimine, hoidmine, kasutamine, m&auml;rgistamine, h&auml;vitamine ja vedu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) "handling of explosive substances" means the manufacture, processing, reprocessing, restoration, packaging, assembly, storage, use, marking, destruction and carriage of explosive substances; </inglise>
<eesti>2) l&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;ive - l&otilde;hkematerjali soetamine, turustamine (m&uuml;&uuml;mine, vastuv&otilde;tmine, tarbija otsimine, tellimine), sisse- ja v&auml;ljavedu, &uuml;leandmine teistele. </eesti>
<inglise>2) "trade in explosive substances" means the procurement, marketing (sale, receipt, locating consumers, ordering), import and export of explosive substances and transfer of explosive substances to others. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vastutav isik m&auml;&auml;ratakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja k&auml;skkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A responsible person shall be appointed by a directive of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemise ja k&auml;ibe eest vastutav isik vastutab selle eest, et l&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemine ja k&auml;ive toimub k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt ning vastab loas esitatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person responsible for the handling of and trade in explosive substances shall ensure that the handling of and trade in explosive substances is conducted according to this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof, and complies with the requirements set out in a permit or licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Enne vastutavaks isikuks m&auml;&auml;ramist peab vastav kandidaat olema atesteeritud Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Prior to being appointed a responsible person, the corresponding candidate shall be evaluated by the Technical Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Atesteerimine on n&otilde;utav j&auml;rgmistel l&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemise ja k&auml;ibe eest vastutavatel isikutel: </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Evaluation of the following persons responsible for the handling of and trade in explosive substances is required: </inglise>
<eesti>1) l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamise eest vastutaval isikul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) persons responsible for the manufacture of explosive substances; </inglise>
<eesti>2) l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise eest vastutaval isikul; </eesti>
<inglise>2) persons responsible for blasting; </inglise>
<eesti>3) l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;relevalve eest vastutaval isikul; </eesti>
<inglise>3) persons responsible for supervision over blasting; </inglise>
<eesti>4) l&otilde;hkematerjali hoidmise ja v&auml;ljastamise eest vastutaval isikul; </eesti>
<inglise>4) persons responsible for the storage and issue of explosive substances; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ilutulestiku korraldamise eest vastutaval isikul; </eesti>
<inglise>5) persons responsible for the organisation of fireworks displays; </inglise>
<eesti>6) l&otilde;hkematerjaliga t&ouml;&ouml;tamise eest vastutaval isikul. </eesti>
<inglise>6) persons responsible for work with explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Vastutava isiku m&auml;&auml;ramine ei vabasta t&ouml;&ouml;andjat ja tegevjuhti isiklikust vastutusest l&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemise ja k&auml;ibe vastavuse eest k&auml;esoleva seadusega ning muude &otilde;igusaktidega s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The appointment of a responsible person does not release an employer or manager from personal liability for the handling of and trade in explosive substances in compliance with requirements provided by this Act or other legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutava isiku atesteerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Evaluation of responsible persons </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutavat isikut atesteerib t&ouml;&ouml;andja suunamisel v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tja taotlusel Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni eksamikomisjon, kes kontrollib kandidaadi tehnilisi ja &otilde;igusalaseid teadmisi ning valmisolekut praktiliseks t&ouml;&ouml;ks. </eesti>
<inglise>Responsible persons are evaluated, upon assignment by employers or at the request of traders by the examination board of the Technical Inspectorate, which assesses the technical and legal knowledge of candidates and their readiness for practical work. </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteeritule v&auml;ljastatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 31 kohaselt tunnistus. </eesti>
<inglise>A certificate shall be issued to persons who successfully pass the evaluation pursuant to &sect; 31 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutava isiku tunnistus </eesti>
<inglise>Certificate of responsible person </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vastutava isiku tunnistuse v&auml;ljastab, pikendab ja t&uuml;histab Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Certificates of a responsible person are issued, renewed and revoked by the Technical Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tunnistus antakse kehtivusega kuni viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Certificates are issued for a term of up to five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tunnistusel peab olema m&auml;rgitud tunnistuse omaniku nimi, tunnistuse v&auml;ljaandmise kuup&auml;ev, l&otilde;petatud &otilde;ppeasutuse nimetus, diplomi v&otilde;i tunnistuse number ja sellega omistatud kvalifikatsioon ning millise vastutava isikuna tunnistuse omanik v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tada. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Certificates shall set out the name of the holder of the certificate, the date of issue of the certificate, the name of the educational institution from which the holder of the certificate has graduated, the number of the diploma or certificate and qualification awarded thereby, and the type of responsible person the holder of the certificate may work as. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tunnistuse v&auml;ljaandja v&otilde;ib kehtivale tunnistusele teha t&auml;iendusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Issuers of certificates may make amendments to valid certificates. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tunnistuse omanik peab v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kord viie aasta jooksul osa v&otilde;tma t&auml;iend&otilde;ppest, mille programm on koosk&otilde;lastatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 60 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatu kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A holder of a certificate shall, not less than once every five years, participate in an in-service training programme, the curriculum of which shall be concorded in accordance with the provisions of subsection 60 (3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;pingute l&auml;bimine on tunnistuse kehtivusaja pikendamise aluseks. </eesti>
<inglise>The completion of such training constitutes the basis for the extension of the term of the certificate. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Tunnistus kaotab kehtivuse, kui selle omanik ei ole p&auml;rast tunnistuse saamist &uuml;he aasta jooksul tunnistusel m&auml;rgitud vastutava isikuna t&ouml;&ouml;le asunud v&otilde;i tal on sellealases tegevuses vaheaeg &uuml;le kahe aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A certificate becomes invalid if the holder has not commenced work as a responsible person indicated in the certificate within one year after the issue of such certificate or if there has been a break of more than two years in his or her activities in such area. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutavate isikute arv ja t&ouml;&ouml;korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Number of responsible persons and organisation of work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vastutavate isikute arv ja kvalifikatsioon peab, s&otilde;ltuvalt ettev&otilde;tte suurusest, tagama l&otilde;hkematerjali ohutu k&auml;itlemise ja k&auml;ibe. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The number and qualification of responsible persons shall, depending on the size of the enterprise, ensure the safe handling of and trade in explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametikohtade loetelu, millel t&ouml;&ouml;tamine &uuml;hitatakse vastutusega m&otilde;nes l&otilde;hkematerjalide k&auml;itlemise v&otilde;i k&auml;ibe valdkonnas, samuti vastutavate isikute arvu m&auml;&auml;rab t&ouml;&ouml;andja koosk&otilde;lastatult Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooniga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employers, in concordance with the Technical Inspectorate, shall determine lists of positions in which employment involves responsibility in some area of handling of or trade in explosive substances, and the number of responsible persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui ettev&otilde;tte omanik v&otilde;i valdaja on &uuml;htlasi m&otilde;ne k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 29 l&otilde;ikes 6 nimetatud tegevusala eest vastutav isik, peab ka tema taotlema atesteerimist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An owner or possessor of an enterprise who is also a person responsible for an activity specified in subsection 29 (6) of this Act shall apply for evaluation. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ettev&otilde;ttesisene t&ouml;&ouml;korraldus peab tagama, et ametikohale m&auml;&auml;ratud vastutav isik saaks t&auml;ita oma etten&auml;htud kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The internal organisation of work shall ensure that responsible persons who are appointed to their positions are able to fulfil their prescribed duties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutavale isikule esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for responsible persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vastutavaks isikuks ei v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;rata isikut, kes: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following shall not be appointed as a responsible person: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&otilde;eb ps&uuml;hhoaktiivsete ainete kasutamisest tingitud ps&uuml;&uuml;hika- v&otilde;i k&auml;itumish&auml;iret; </eesti>
<inglise>1) persons suffering from mental or behavioural disorders caused by the use of psychoactive substances; </inglise>
<eesti>2) p&otilde;eb rasket v&otilde;i pikaajalist ps&uuml;&uuml;hikah&auml;iret, mis on vastun&auml;idustuseks l&otilde;hkematerjalidega t&ouml;&ouml;tamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) persons suffering from severe or long-term mental disorders due to which work with explosive substances is contraindicated; </inglise>
<eesti>3) on tunnistatud teov&otilde;imetuks v&otilde;i tema teov&otilde;imet on piiratud; </eesti>
<inglise>3) persons who are divested of active legal capacity or whose active legal capacity is restricted; </inglise>
<eesti>4) on kriminaalkorras karistatud tahtlikult toimepandud esimese astme kuriteo eest, olenemata sellest, kas karistatus on kustunud v&otilde;i kustutatud; </eesti>
<inglise>4) persons who have been punished under criminal procedure for an intentionally committed crime in the first degree, regardless of whether the criminal record has expired or been expunged; </inglise>
<eesti>5) omab karistatust muu kuriteo toimepanemise eest; </eesti>
<inglise>5) persons with a criminal record for the commission of any other criminal offence; </inglise>
<eesti>6) on kriminaalkorras karistatud kuriteo eest, mille p&otilde;hjustas hooletu &uuml;mberk&auml;imine relva, laskemoona v&otilde;i l&otilde;hkematerjaliga, olenemata sellest, kas karistatus on kustunud v&otilde;i kustutatud; </eesti>
<inglise>6) persons who have been punished under criminal procedure for a criminal offence caused by the careless handling of weapons, ammunition or explosive substances, regardless of whether the criminal record has expired or been expunged; </inglise>
<eesti>7) on kriminaalmenetlusest tulenevatel alustel kuulutatud tagaotsitavaks v&otilde;i v&otilde;etud vastutusele kahtlustatavana, s&uuml;&uuml;distatavana v&otilde;i kohtualusena; </eesti>
<inglise>7) persons declared to be a fugitive on grounds arising from criminal proceedings or who have been brought to justice as a suspect, accused or accused at trial; </inglise>
<eesti>8) on eelnenud aasta jooksul v&auml;hemalt kaks korda karistatud halduskorras, millest &uuml;ks oli haldusarest. </eesti>
<inglise>8) persons who have been punished during the preceding year under administrative proceedings on at least two occasions, where one of the punishments was administrative detention. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vastutavale isikule esitatakse j&auml;rgmised haridusn&otilde;uded: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following requirements are set for the education of responsible persons: </inglise>
<eesti>1) l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamise eest vastutav isik peab olema k&otilde;rg- v&otilde;i keskeriharidusega l&otilde;hkeainete keemik-tehnoloog, samuti m&auml;einsener v&otilde;i m&auml;etehnik, kes on l&otilde;petanud kursuse l&otilde;hkeainete tehnoloogia erialal; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a person responsible for the manufacture of explosive substances shall be an explosives chemist with higher or vocational secondary education, or a mining engineer or mining technician who has completed a course in explosives technology; </inglise>
<eesti>2) l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;de tegemise eest vastutaval isikul peab olema m&auml;etehniline k&otilde;rg- v&otilde;i keskeriharidus; m&auml;etehnilise hariduse puudumisel peab ta olema l&otilde;petanud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 60 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatu kohaselt koosk&otilde;lastatud programmi j&auml;rgi l&auml;biviidud kursuse ja praktilise &otilde;ppuse, &uuml;htlasi peab tal olema kuuekuuline praktiline staa&zcaron; l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;de valdkonnas t&ouml;&ouml;tamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a person responsible for blasting shall have higher education or vocational secondary education in mining technology; in the absence of an education in mining, such person shall have completed a course and field training conducted in compliance with a curriculum concorded pursuant to the provisions of subsection 60 (3) of this Act, and have six months of practical experience in blasting; </inglise>
<eesti>3) l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;de j&auml;relevalve eest vastutaval isikul peab olema k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 2 n&otilde;utav haridus, praktiline staa&zcaron; ei ole n&otilde;utav; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a person responsible for supervision over blasting shall have the education required in clause (2) 2) of this section, but practical experience is not required; </inglise>
<eesti>4) l&otilde;hkematerjali hoidmise ja v&auml;ljastamise eest vastutaval isikul peab olema m&auml;einseneri, m&auml;etehniku v&otilde;i l&otilde;hkematerjali laojuhataja kvalifikatsioon; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a person responsible for the storage and issue of explosive substances shall be qualified as a mining engineer, mining technician or head of an explosive substances store; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ilutulestiku korraldamise eest vastutaval isikul peab olema l&otilde;hkeainete keemik-tehnoloogi v&otilde;i p&uuml;rotehniku kvalifikatsioon; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a person responsible for the organisation of fireworks displays shall be qualified as an explosives chemist or pyrotechnician; </inglise>
<eesti>6) l&otilde;hkematerjaliga t&ouml;&ouml;tamise eest vastutaval isikul peab olema l&otilde;hkeainete keemik-tehnoloogi v&otilde;i m&auml;einseneri kvalifikatsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>6) a person responsible for work with explosive substances shall be qualified as an explosives chemist or mining engineer; </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib erandkorras m&ouml;&ouml;nda ka atesteeritava isiku teisi kvalifikatsioone, kui ta on l&otilde;petanud vastava kursuse ja tal on suuri praktilise t&ouml;&ouml; kogemusi selles tegevusvaldkonnas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Technical Inspectorate may, as an exception, recognise other qualifications of a person under evaluation if he or she has completed an appropriate course and has extensive practical experience in such area of activity. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutava isiku tunnistuse t&uuml;histamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of certificate of responsible person </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tunnistuse v&otilde;ib t&uuml;histada, kui tunnistuse omanik: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A certificate may be revoked if the holder of the certificate: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ei vasta enam k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 33 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) no longer complies with the requirements provided for in subsection 33 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) on k&auml;sitsenud l&otilde;hkematerjale alkoholijoobes, narkootilise, ps&uuml;hhotroopse v&otilde;i toksilise aine m&otilde;ju all; </eesti>
<inglise>2) has handled explosive substances while intoxicated or under the influence of narcotic, psychotropic or toxic substances; </inglise>
<eesti>3) on hooletuse v&otilde;i lohakuse t&otilde;ttu lasknud l&otilde;hkematerjali kaotsi minna v&otilde;i k&otilde;lbmatuks muutuda; </eesti>
<inglise>3) has allowed explosive substances to be lost or become unserviceable through his or her carelessness or neglect; </inglise>
<eesti>4) on korduvalt rikkunud t&ouml;&ouml;distsipliini ja ohutuseeskirju; </eesti>
<inglise>4) has repeatedly violated work discipline or safety instructions; </inglise>
<eesti>5) on l&otilde;hkematerjali kasutamisel rikkunud k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;udeid, kuid sellega ei kaasnenud haldus- v&otilde;i kriminaalvastutust. </eesti>
<inglise>5) has violated the requirements of this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof in the use of explosive substances, but no administrative or criminal liability has resulted from such violation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tunnistus t&uuml;histatakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;i j&auml;relevalveorgani taotlusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A certificate shall be revoked at the request of an employer or a supervisory authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tunnistuse t&uuml;histamise otsuse peale v&otilde;ib esitada kaebuse kohtule seaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An appeal concerning a decision to revoke a certificate may be filed with a court pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali kasutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Use of Explosive Substances </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali kasutamise &uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General provisions for use of explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;d v&otilde;ib teha, l&otilde;hkematerjaliga t&ouml;&ouml;tada ja ilutulestikku korraldada asutus v&otilde;i isik, kellel on selleks etten&auml;htud korras antud vastav luba. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An agency or person that holds an appropriate permit issued pursuant to the prescribed procedure may engage in blasting, work with explosive substances or organise fireworks displays. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Loa l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks, l&otilde;hkematerjaliga t&ouml;&ouml;tamiseks ja ilutulestiku korraldamiseks annab, muudab, peatab v&otilde;i t&uuml;histab Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Permits for blasting operations, work with explosive substances and organisation of fireworks displays are issued, amended, suspended and revoked by the Technical Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Paugutite kasutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Use of crackers </inglise>
<eesti>Paugutite kasutamine on keelatud alates 1. novembrist kuni 30. detsembrini (kaasa arvatud). </eesti>
<inglise>The use of crackers is prohibited from 1 November to 30 December (inclusive). </inglise>
<eesti>(10.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.10.2001 entered into force 01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise luba </eesti>
<inglise>Permit for blasting operations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise luba antakse ettev&otilde;ttele, kellel on l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise eest vastutav isik l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; juhtimiseks, l&otilde;hkaja l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks ja ladu l&otilde;hkematerjali hoidmiseks v&otilde;i rendileping l&otilde;hkematerjalilao kasutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A permit for blasting operations is issued to an enterprise which has a person responsible for blasting operations to direct blasting, a blaster to conduct blasting, and a store for the storage of explosive substances or a commercial lease contract for the use of an explosive substances store. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise loaga m&auml;&auml;ratakse piirkond, kus ettev&otilde;te v&otilde;ib l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;d teha, ja l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; lubatav liik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The area in which an enterprise may perform blasting operations and the permitted type of blasting are determined in a permit for blasting operations. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemine peab olema koosk&otilde;lastatud linna- v&otilde;i vallavalitsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Blasting operations shall be concorded with the city or rural municipality government. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise luba antakse t&auml;htajatuna ning see kehtib seni, kuni muutub ettev&otilde;tte nimi, vahetub l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise eest vastutav isik v&otilde;i l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemisel esineb k&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide selliseid rikkumisi, mis tingivad loa t&uuml;histamise. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A permit for blasting operations is issued without a term and is valid until the name of the enterprise is changed, the person responsible for blasting operations is changed, or a violation of this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof is committed in the course of blasting operations which brings about the revocation of the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Enne l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise loa v&auml;ljastamist kontrollib Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon ettev&otilde;tte valmisolekut l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;ks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Before the issue of a permit for blasting operations, the Technical Inspectorate shall assess the preparedness of the enterprise to conduct blasting. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjaliga t&ouml;&ouml;tamise luba </eesti>
<inglise>Permit for work with explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjaliga t&ouml;&ouml;tamise luba antakse ettev&otilde;ttele v&otilde;i asutusele, kes tegeleb l&otilde;hkematerjali katsetamisega, metalli v&otilde;i muu materjali t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisega plahvatuse abil, laskemoona valmistamisega v&otilde;i muu tegevusega, mis eeldab plahvatuse kasutamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A permit for work with explosive substances is issued to an enterprise or agency which is engaged in testing explosive substances, processing metal or other materials with the aid of explosion, manufacturing ammunition or other activities which require the use of explosion. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali kasutaval ettev&otilde;ttel v&otilde;i asutusel peab olema l&otilde;hkematerjaliga t&ouml;&ouml;tamise eest vastutav isik nende t&ouml;&ouml;de juhtimiseks, laborant katsetuste tegemiseks ja koht l&otilde;hkematerjali hoidmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An enterprise or agency which uses explosive substances shall have a person responsible for work with explosive substances to direct such work, a laboratory assistant to conduct the tests and a place for the storage of explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Ilutulestiku korraldamise luba </eesti>
<inglise>Permit for organisation of fireworks displays </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ilutulestik k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes on vaatem&auml;ng, mis p&otilde;hineb p&uuml;rotehniliste ainete p&otilde;lemisel tekkivatel valgusefektidel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, a fireworks display is a display of light effects arising from the combustion of pyrotechnic substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ilutulestiku korraldamise luba on n&otilde;utav III, IV v&otilde;i T1 klassi p&uuml;rotehniliste toodete kasutamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A permit for the organisation of fireworks displays is required for the use of pyrotechnic articles of divisions III, IV and T1. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ilutulestiku korraldamise luba antakse asutustele, f&uuml;&uuml;silisele v&otilde;i juriidilisele isikule, kellel on ilutulestiku korraldamise eest vastutav isik ja tingimused p&uuml;rotehniliste toodete hoidmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A permit for the organisation of fireworks displays is issued to agencies and natural or legal persons with a person responsible for the organisation of fireworks displays and the required conditions for the storage of pyrotechnic articles. </inglise>
<eesti>Ilutulestiku tegemiseks IV klassi p&uuml;rotehniliste toodetega peab olema p&uuml;rotehnik. </eesti>
<inglise>Fireworks displays where pyrotechnic articles of division IV are used shall be conducted by a pyrotechnician. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Iga konkreetse ilutulestiku tegemiseks peab ilutulestikku korraldav isik v&otilde;i asutus saama linna- v&otilde;i vallavalitsuse n&otilde;usoleku koosk&otilde;lastatult tulet&otilde;rjej&auml;relevalve ja politseiprefektuuriga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person or agency which organises fireworks displays shall obtain consent to conduct each specific fireworks display from the city or rural municipality government in concordance with the fire fighting supervisory body and the Police Prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; luba </eesti>
<inglise>Blasting permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; luba antakse l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise loa omanikule, kui ta soovib l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;d teha asulas, ehitise purustamisel, metalli t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisel v&otilde;i purustamisel, vee all ja massl&otilde;hkamisel (&uuml;le &uuml;he tonni l&otilde;hkeainet korraga). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A blasting permit is issued to a holder of a permit for blasting operations if the holder of the permit wishes to conduct blasting operations in a settlement, in the demolition of structures or the processing of metal or breaking up of metal into pieces, or to conduct underwater or mass blasting (where more than one tonne of explosives is used at once). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; loa saamiseks peab loa taotleja esitama Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioonile avalduse, millele lisatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to obtain a blasting permit, the applicant for the permit shall submit an application to the Technical Inspectorate to which the following shall be appended: </inglise>
<eesti>1) l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; projekt; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the blasting plan; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maakoha plaan m&otilde;&otilde;tkavas 1: 500 kuni 1: 10000, kuhu on m&auml;rgitud l&otilde;hatav objekt ja l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; ohtliku ala piirid koos valvepostide paigutusega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a plan of the area on a scale of between 1: 500 and 1: 10000 on which the site to be blasted, the boundaries of the blasting danger zone and the location of guard posts are indicated; </inglise>
<eesti>3) linna- v&otilde;i vallavalitsuse n&otilde;usolek ja keskkonnatalituse ning ohtlikku alasse j&auml;&auml;va ettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i asutuse koosk&otilde;lastus ja tingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the consent of the city or rural municipality government, and the concordance of and conditions imposed by the environmental division of the local government, and enterprises and agencies located within the danger zone. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 3 n&auml;idatud koosk&otilde;lastused v&otilde;ib teha ka maakoha plaanile. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The concordances set out in clause (2) 3) of this section may also be marked on the plan of the area. </inglise>
<eesti>Koosk&otilde;lastusest keeldumisel tuleb m&auml;rkida selle p&otilde;hjus. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon refusal to grant concordance, the reason for refusal shall be indicated. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; luba antakse kehtivusega kuni &uuml;ks aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A blasting permit is issued for a term of up to one year. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa kehtivuse t&auml;htaega v&otilde;ib pikendada, kui l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; ohtliku ala piirid ja l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tehnilised tingimused ei ole muutunud. </eesti>
<inglise>The term of a permit may be extended if the boundaries of the blasting danger zone and the technical requirements for blasting have not changed. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudel juhtudel on vajalik uus l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; luba. </eesti>
<inglise>In other cases a new blasting permit is required. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; luba ei ole n&otilde;utav, kui maavara tootev ettev&otilde;te teeb ise maavara kaevandamiseks vajalikku massl&otilde;hkamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A blasting permit is not required if a mineral resources processing enterprise itself conducts the mass blasting necessary for mining mineral resources. </inglise>
<eesti>Massl&otilde;hkamise vajadusel tuleb k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 36 s&auml;testatud l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise loa taotlemisel lisada k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>If mass blasting is required, the documents provided for in subsection (2) of this section shall be appended to the application for a permit for blasting operations provided for in &sect; 36 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; ohtlik ala ei &uuml;leta maa-ala piire, millele maavara tootval v&otilde;i l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;d tellival ettev&otilde;ttel on kasutamis&otilde;igus ja kaevandamisloa v&auml;ljaandja ei ole andnud lisatingimusi, ei ole k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 3 etten&auml;htud n&otilde;usolek ja koosk&otilde;lastused vajalikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The consent and concordances prescribed in clause (2) 3) of this section are not necessary if the blasting danger zone does not exceed the boundaries of the area to which a mineral resources processing enterprise or the enterprise which ordered the blasting has a right of use and if the issuer of the extraction permit does not impose additional conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; loa v&auml;ljaandmisest keeldumine </eesti>
<inglise>Refusal to issue blasting permit </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; luba ei anta, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>A blasting permit shall not be issued if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) koosk&otilde;lastusega antud n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmine viib k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 60 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; ohutuseeskirja rikkumisele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) compliance with conditions imposed by a concordance would result in a violation of the safety rules for blasting provided for in subsection 60 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; projektis etten&auml;htud abin&otilde;ud ei taga inimeste, vara ja keskkonna ohutust. </eesti>
<inglise>2) measures prescribed by the blasting plan fail to ensure the safety of people, property and the environment. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegija </eesti>
<inglise>Person engaging in blasting </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;d v&otilde;ib teha ainult l&otilde;hkaja kutsetunnistust omav isik (edaspidi l&otilde;hkaja). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Only persons who hold a blaster's certificate (hereinafter blaster) may conduct blasting. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkajana v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tada Eesti kodanik, samuti alalise v&otilde;i t&auml;htajalise elamisloa alusel Eestis viibiv v&auml;lismaalane, kes on v&auml;hemalt 19-aastane, t&ouml;&ouml;tanud &uuml;he aasta l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; l&auml;hiprofiilil olevatel t&ouml;&ouml;del, kellel ei esine k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 33 l&otilde;ikes 1 loetletud asjaolusid ning ta on l&auml;binud eelneva tervisekontrolli, mille j&auml;reldusotsus ei v&auml;lista l&otilde;hkajana t&ouml;&ouml;tamist, on l&otilde;petanud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 60 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaselt kinnitatud programmi j&auml;rgi l&auml;biviidud kursused ja sooritanud eksami Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni kvalifikatsioonikomisjonis ning saanud l&otilde;hkaja kutsetunnistuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An Estonian citizen or an alien residing in Estonia on the basis of a permanent or temporary residence permit, who has attained nineteen years of age and has engaged in work closely related to blasting for a period of one year, to whom the circumstances listed in subsection 33 (1) of this Act do not apply, who has undergone a prior medical examination the results of which do not exclude work as a blaster, who has completed a course conducted according to a curriculum approved pursuant to subsection 60 (3) of this Act, has passed an examination of the Professional Qualifications Board of the Technical Inspectorate and has been issued a blaster's certificate, may work as a blaster. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkaja kutse taotleja peab l&auml;bima eelneva tervisekontrolli ja l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegija perioodilise tervisekontrolli sotsiaalministri poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Persons applying for qualification as a blaster shall undergo a prior medical examination and persons engaging in blasting shall undergo routine medical examinations pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;hkajana v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tada ka isik, kes on k&otilde;rgkoolis v&otilde;i kutse&otilde;ppeasutuses edukalt l&auml;binud programmilise l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;de &otilde;ppuse, t&ouml;&ouml;tanud seej&auml;rel v&auml;hemalt kaks kuud l&otilde;hkaja abina ja sooritanud eksami Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni kvalifikatsioonikomisjonis. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person who has successfully completed a blasting course prescribed by a curriculum in an institute of higher education or a vocational institution, has worked as an assistant blaster for not less than two months thereafter and passed an examination of the Professional Qualifications Board of the Technical Inspectorate may work as a blaster. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) V&auml;lismaal l&otilde;hkaja kutse&otilde;petuse l&auml;binud l&otilde;hkaja peab sooritama eksami Eesti l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;alaste &otilde;igusaktide tundmises. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A blaster who has undergone the vocational training of a blaster abroad shall pass an examination on Estonian legislation concerning blasting. </inglise>
<eesti>Eestis seaduslikult viibiv v&auml;lismaalane v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tada l&otilde;hkajana, kui tal on l&otilde;hkaja kutsetunnistus, Eestis t&ouml;&ouml;tamise luba ja ta on sooritanud eksami Eesti l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;alaste &otilde;igusaktide tundmises. </eesti>
<inglise>An alien legally in Estonia may work as a blaster if he or she holds a blaster's certificate and a permit for working in Estonia and has passed an examination on Estonian legislation concerning blasting. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) L&otilde;hkaja v&otilde;ib teha ainult kutsetunnistusel m&auml;rgitud l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Blasters may only perform the blasting operations indicated on their blaster's certificates. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) L&otilde;hkaja kutsetunnistus kehtib viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A blaster's certificate is valid for five years. </inglise>
<eesti>Selle kehtivuse pikendamiseks peab l&otilde;hkaja l&auml;bi tegema t&auml;iend&otilde;ppe ja sooritama eksami Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioonis. </eesti>
<inglise>In order to extend the term, a blaster shall complete in-service training and pass an examination of the Technical Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutsetunnistus muutub kehtetuks, kui selle omanik ei ole aasta jooksul asunud t&ouml;&ouml;tama sellel kutsealal v&otilde;i kui tema t&ouml;&ouml;katkestus l&otilde;hkajana on kestnud &uuml;le kahe aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>A blaster's certificate becomes invalid if the holder thereof has not commenced work as a blaster within one year or his or her work as a blaster has been interrupted for more than two years. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) L&otilde;hkaja v&otilde;ib p&auml;rast aastast t&ouml;&ouml;tamist, kui ta on v&auml;hemalt 21-aastane, taotleda l&otilde;hkemeistri kvalifikatsiooni, mis annab talle &otilde;iguse teha l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;d iseseisvalt l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;de j&auml;relevalve eest vastutava isiku juuresolekuta, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 39 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) A blaster who has attained twenty-one years of age may, after one year of work, apply for the qualification of senior blaster, which grants him or her the right to perform blasting operations independently without the presence of a person responsible for supervision over blasting, except in the cases provided in subsection 39 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) L&otilde;hkemeistri kvalifikatsiooni saamiseks peab l&otilde;hkaja l&auml;bi tegema t&auml;iend&otilde;ppe ja sooritama eksami Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioonis. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) In order to obtain the qualification of senior blaster, a blaster shall complete in-service training and pass an examination of the Technical Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkemeistri kvalifikatsioon m&auml;rgitakse l&otilde;hkaja kutsetunnistusele. </eesti>
<inglise>The qualification of senior blaster shall be indicated on the blaster's certificate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali v&auml;ljastaja </eesti>
<inglise>Issuer of explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali v&otilde;ib lattu hoiule v&otilde;tta ja laost v&auml;ljastada l&otilde;hkematerjalilao juhataja ja l&otilde;hkematerjali v&auml;ljastaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Heads of explosive substances stores and issuers of explosive substances may receive explosive substances into a store for storage and issue explosive substances from the store. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjalilao juhataja ja tema asendaja peavad olema atesteeritud l&otilde;hkematerjali hoidmise ja v&auml;ljastamise eest vastutava isikuna. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Heads of explosive substances stores and their substitutes shall have undergone evaluation as a person responsible for the storage and issue of explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkematerjalilao juhatajal peab olema m&auml;einseneri v&otilde;i tehniku kvalifikatsioon v&otilde;i ta peab olema l&otilde;petanud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 60 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaselt kinnitatud programmi j&auml;rgi l&auml;biviidud kursuse, sooritanud eksami Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni kvalifikatsioonikomisjonis ja saanud l&otilde;hkematerjalilao juhataja kutsetunnistuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A head of an explosive substances store shall be qualified as a mining engineer or mining technician or shall have completed a course conducted according to a curriculum approved pursuant to subsection 60 (3) of this Act, passed an examination of the Professional Qualifications Board of the Technical Inspectorate and been issued a certificate of qualification as a head of an explosive substances store. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;hkematerjali v&auml;ljastajana v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tada isik, kellel on kas l&otilde;hkematerjalilao juhataja kutsetunnistus v&otilde;i on ta l&otilde;petanud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 60 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaselt kinnitatud programmi j&auml;rgi l&auml;biviidud kursused, sooritanud eksami Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni kvalifikatsioonikomisjonis ja saanud l&otilde;hkematerjali v&auml;ljastaja kutsetunnistuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person holding a certificate of qualification as a head of an explosive substances store or who has completed a course conducted according to a curriculum approved pursuant to subsection 60 (3) of this Act, passed an examination of the Professional Qualifications Board of the Technical Inspectorate and been issued a certificate of qualification as an issuer of explosive substances may work as an issuer of explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) P&uuml;rotehniliste toodete lao juhatajaks v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata isiku, kellel on l&otilde;hkematerjali v&auml;ljastaja kutsetunnistus, tema atesteerimine ei ole n&otilde;utav. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A person holding a certificate of qualification as an issuer of explosive substances may be appointed head of a pyrotechnic articles store, and the evaluation of such person is not required. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali laborant </eesti>
<inglise>Explosive substances laboratory assistant </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali laborandiks on k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes isik, kes katsetab l&otilde;hkematerjali v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tleb metalle v&otilde;i muid materjale plahvatuse abil. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, an explosive substances laboratory assistant is a person who tests explosive substances or processes metal or other materials by explosion. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali laborandina v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 41 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatu j&auml;rgi v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe ja kutsetunnistuse saanud isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who has completed training and has been issued a professional certificate pursuant to the provisions of subsection 41 (2) of this Act may work as an explosive substances laboratory assistant. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutsetunnistuse &auml;rav&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of professional certificate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkajalt, l&otilde;hkematerjalilao juhatajalt, l&otilde;hkematerjali v&auml;ljastajalt v&otilde;i laborandilt v&otilde;ib kutsetunnistuse &auml;ra v&otilde;tta, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The professional certificate of a blaster, head of an explosive substances store, issuer of explosive substances or explosive substances laboratory assistant may be revoked if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ta on sooritanud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 33 l&otilde;ikes 1 loetletud &otilde;iguserikkumise; </eesti>
<inglise>1) he or she commits an offence listed in subsection 33 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tema tegevus p&otilde;hjustas raske v&otilde;i surmaga l&otilde;ppenud t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse v&otilde;i avarii; </eesti>
<inglise>2) his or her actions cause a serious or fatal accident at work or other accident; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ta on korduvalt rikkunud ohutuseeskirjade n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>3) he or she repeatedly violates the requirements of safety rules. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kutsetunnistuse v&otilde;ib &auml;ra v&otilde;tta politseiasutuse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja taotlusel, samuti j&auml;relevalvet teostava ametiisiku poolt avastatud ohutuseeskirjade rikkumiste korral Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A professional certificate may be revoked by the Technical Inspectorate at the request of a police authority or an employer or if an official conducting supervision discovers violations of safety rules. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatu alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tajalt &auml;rav&otilde;etud kutsetunnistuse v&otilde;ib ennistada p&auml;rast kutseeksami sooritamist Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioonis, kuid mitte enne kolme kuu m&ouml;&ouml;dumist kutsetunnistuse &auml;rav&otilde;tmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The professional certificate of an employee which is revoked on the basis of the provisions of clauses (1) 2) or 3) of this section may be restored after the employee passes a professional examination of the Technical Inspectorate, but not earlier than three months after the revocation of the professional certificate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali h&auml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Destruction of explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Standardi v&otilde;i tehniliste tingimuste n&otilde;uetele mittevastav, samuti leitud l&otilde;hkematerjal kuulub h&auml;vitamisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Explosive substances which do not comply with standards or technical requirements and explosive substances which are found are subject to destruction. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Leitud l&otilde;hkematerjal antakse h&auml;vitamiseks &uuml;le P&auml;&auml;steametile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Explosive substances which are found shall be delivered to the Rescue Service Administration for destruction. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;kohas tuleb h&auml;vitada t&otilde;rke andnud ja t&otilde;rke likvideerimisel mitteplahvatanud l&otilde;hkematerjal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Misfired explosive substances and explosive substances which do not explode upon liquidation of a misfire shall be destroyed at the jobsite. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;hkematerjalitehases v&otilde;ib l&otilde;hkematerjali h&auml;vitada l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamise eest vastutava isiku, l&otilde;hkematerjalilaos l&otilde;hkematerjali hoidmise ja v&auml;ljastamise eest vastutava isiku ja t&ouml;&ouml;kohas l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise v&otilde;i l&otilde;hkematerjaliga t&ouml;&ouml;tamise eest vastutava isiku korraldusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Explosive substances may be destroyed at an explosive substances plant on the order of a person responsible for the manufacture of explosive substances, at an explosive substances store on the order of a person responsible for the storage and issue of explosive substances, and at a jobsite on the order of a person responsible for blasting or a person responsible for work with explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) L&otilde;hkematerjali v&otilde;ib h&auml;vitada l&otilde;hkaja v&otilde;i l&otilde;hkematerjali laborandi kutsetunnistust omav isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Explosive substances may be destroyed by persons holding a blaster's certificate or certificate of qualification as an explosive substances laboratory assistant. </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali vedu </eesti>
<inglise>Carriage of Explosive Substances </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali vedu raudtee-, &otilde;hu- ja veetranspordiga </eesti>
<inglise>Carriage of explosive substances by rail, air and waterway </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali vedu raudtee-, &otilde;hu- ja veetranspordiga toimub vastavat veoliiki k&auml;sitlevate seaduste ja nende alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Carriage of explosive substances by rail, air and waterway shall be effected pursuant to the procedure provided for in Acts concerning the corresponding mode of transport and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali autovedu &uuml;ldkasutatavatel teedel </eesti>
<inglise>Carriage of explosive substances by vehicle on public roads </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali autovedu &uuml;ldiseks liikluseks avatud teedel toimub liiklusseaduse (RT 1992, 12, 193; RT I 1995, 2/3, 3; 1996, 16, 268) ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Carriage of explosive substances by vehicle on roads open for general traffic shall be effected pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Traffic Act (RT 1992, 12, 193; RT I 1995, 2/3, 3; 1996, 16, 268) and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali autovedu v&otilde;ib teostada l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamisluba, m&uuml;&uuml;giluba v&otilde;i soetusluba omav isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Carriage of explosive substances by vehicle may be performed by persons who hold a permit for the manufacture of an explosive substance, an explosive substances sales permit or an explosive substances procurement permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkematerjali vedaval autol peab olema kaks juhti, kellel on l&otilde;hkematerjali vedamiseks vastav kvalifikatsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A vehicle carrying explosive substances shall have two drivers, both of whom shall be appropriately qualified for the carriage of explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui l&otilde;hkaja saadab l&otilde;hkematerjali vedavat veo&uuml;hikut l&otilde;hkematerjali veol laost t&ouml;&ouml;kohta, v&otilde;ib l&otilde;hkematerjali saatekirja asemel olla t&ouml;&ouml;k&auml;sk. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a blaster accompanies a transport unit carrying explosive substances from a store to a jobsite, an explosive substances way-bill may be substituted by a work order. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali vedu koguses, mis ei &uuml;leta vabapiiriga m&auml;&auml;ratut </eesti>
<inglise>Carriage of explosive substances in quantities not exceeding limit values </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vabapiir on k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes l&otilde;hkematerjali suurim lubatud netomass &uuml;hes veo&uuml;hikus, mille vedamisel ohtlikele veostele kehtestatud piirangud ei ole kohustuslikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, a limit value is the maximum permissible net mass of explosive substances in one transport unit, with regard to the carriage of which restrictions established for hazardous loads are not mandatory. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) S&otilde;ltuvalt sobivusr&uuml;hmast on l&otilde;hkematerjali vabapiir ja ohutegur j&auml;rgmised: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The limit values and risk factors of explosive substances, depending on compatibility group, are as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) A sobivusr&uuml;hmal 5 kg ohuteguriga 200; </eesti>
<inglise>1) for compatibility group A, 5 kilograms with a risk factor of 200; </inglise>
<eesti>2) B sobivusr&uuml;hmal 20 kg ohuteguriga 50; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for compatibility group B, 20 kilograms with a risk factor of 50; </inglise>
<eesti>3) C sobivusr&uuml;hmal 50 kg ohuteguriga 20; </eesti>
<inglise>3) for compatibility group C, 50 kilograms with a risk factor of 20; </inglise>
<eesti>4) D sobivusr&uuml;hmal 50 kg ohuteguriga 20; </eesti>
<inglise>4) for compatibility group D, 50 kilograms with a risk factor of 20; </inglise>
<eesti>5) E sobivusr&uuml;hmal 333 kg ohuteguriga 3; </eesti>
<inglise>5) for compatibility group E, 333 kilograms with a risk factor of 3; </inglise>
<eesti>6) F sobivusr&uuml;hmal 500 kg ohuteguriga 2; </eesti>
<inglise>6) for compatibility group F, 500 kilograms with a risk factor of 2; </inglise>
<eesti>7) G sobivusr&uuml;hmal 1000 kg ohuteguriga 1. </eesti>
<inglise>7) for compatibility group G, 1000 kilograms with a risk factor of 1. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Erinevate sobivusr&uuml;hmade l&otilde;hkematerjalide koosveol ei tohi veetavate l&otilde;hkematerjalide netomasside ja ohutegurite korrutiste summa olla &uuml;le 1000. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon the mixed carriage of explosive substances belonging to different compatibility groups, the product of the net mass of explosive substances carried multiplied by the appropriate risk factor shall not exceed 1000. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) A sobivusr&uuml;hma l&otilde;hkematerjali ei tohi vedada koos mistahes teise l&otilde;hkematerjaliga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Explosive substances of compatibility group A shall not be carried together with any other explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) L&otilde;hkematerjali veol peab autojuht olema varustatud sidevahendiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon the carriage of explosive substances, the driver of a vehicle shall be equipped with means of communication. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Veo&uuml;hikul peab olema &uuml;ks k&auml;situlekustuti, mille minimaalne maht on 2 kg kuiva pulbrit v&otilde;i samav&auml;&auml;rses koguses kustutusainet. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A transport unit shall be equipped with one portable fire extinguisher with a minimum volume of 2 kilograms of dry powder or an equivalent amount of extinguishing agent. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali autovedu &uuml;ldiseks liikluseks suletud teel ja territooriumil </eesti>
<inglise>Carriage of explosive substances by vehicle on roads and territories closed to general traffic </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;ldiseks liikluseks suletud teel v&otilde;i territooriumil v&otilde;ib l&otilde;hkematerjali autovedu toimuda ainult tee v&otilde;i territooriumi omaniku v&otilde;i haldaja loal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Carriage of explosive substances by vehicle on a road or territory closed to general traffic may be effected only with the permission of the person who owns or maintains the road or territory. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali autoveol &uuml;ldiseks liikluseks suletud teel ja territooriumil vabapiiri &uuml;letavas koguses kehtivad j&auml;rgmised n&otilde;uded: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following requirements apply to the carriage of explosive substances by vehicle on roads and territories closed to general traffic in amounts exceeding the limit values: </inglise>
<eesti>1) autojuhil peab olema ohtlike veoste veo autojuhi koolituse tunnistus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the driver of a vehicle shall hold a certificate of training as a driver of vehicles carrying hazardous loads; </inglise>
<eesti>2) veo&uuml;hik peab olema m&auml;rgistatud ohtlike veoste tunnusm&auml;rgi ja ohum&auml;rgisega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) transport units shall be marked with an identification plate of hazardous loads and a danger label; </inglise>
<eesti>3) veokis peab olema l&otilde;hkematerjali saatev isik, kellel on l&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemise &otilde;igus ja saatekiri v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;k&auml;sk; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a person accompanying the explosive substances shall be in the vehicle, and he or she shall have the right to handle explosive substances and a way-bill or work order; </inglise>
<eesti>4) veoseruum ei tohi olla kallutatav; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the cargo space shall not be tilted; </inglise>
<eesti>5) veo&uuml;hikus peab olema &uuml;ks k&auml;situlekustuti, mille minimaalne maht on 6 kg kuiva pulbrit (v&otilde;i samav&auml;&auml;rses koguses kustutusainet); </eesti>
<inglise>5) transport units shall be equipped with one portable fire extinguisher with a minimum content of 6 kilograms of dry powder (or an equivalent amount of extinguishing agent); </inglise>
<eesti>6) veoki peab olema lubanud l&otilde;hkematerjali veole auto tehnoseisundi eest vastutav isik. </eesti>
<inglise>6) permission for a vehicle to carry explosive substances shall have been given by the person responsible for the technical condition of the vehicle. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali pakend </eesti>
<inglise>Packaging of explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali v&auml;lispakend peab olema selliselt valmistatud ja suletud, et normaalsete veotingimuste korral esineva vibratsiooni, temperatuuri k&otilde;ikumise, niiskuse ja r&otilde;hu toimel sisepakendist selle sisu v&auml;lja ei tuleks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The outer packaging of explosive substances shall be manufactured and sealed in a manner which precludes the leaking of the contents from the inner packaging due to vibration, fluctuations in temperature, humidity or pressure occurring under normal carriage conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pakendi v&auml;lisk&uuml;lgedel ei tohi olla l&otilde;hkematerjali j&auml;lgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) No traces of explosive substances shall be present on the outer surfaces of a package. </inglise>
<eesti>Selline n&otilde;ue kehtib ka korduvkasutatava pakendi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>This requirement also applies to recoverable packaging. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Pakendi osad, mis on vahetult kontaktis l&otilde;hkeainega, ei tohi sellega keemiliselt reageerida. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Parts of packaging which are in direct contact with explosives shall not react chemically with the explosives. </inglise>
<eesti>Vajaduse korral tuleb pakendi sisek&uuml;ljed vastava ainega katta v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;delda. </eesti>
<inglise>If necessary, the inner surfaces of packaging shall be covered or treated with appropriate substances. </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemise ja k&auml;ibega tegeleva isiku ning asutuse kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of Persons and Agencies Engaged in Handling of and Trade in Explosive Substances </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Avariist, t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetusest ja l&otilde;hkematerjali kaotsiminekust teatamine ning nende uurimine </eesti>
<inglise>Notification of accidents, accidents at work and loss of explosive substances, and investigation thereof </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemisel v&otilde;i k&auml;ibel toimunud avariist v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetusest, mis p&otilde;hjustas t&ouml;&ouml;taja surma, raske tervisekahjustuse v&otilde;i tervisekahjustuse kahele v&otilde;i enamale t&ouml;&ouml;tajale, peab t&ouml;&ouml;andja viivitamatult teatama asukohaj&auml;rgsele politseiasutusele, T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsioonile ja Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer shall promptly notify the local police authority, Labour Inspectorate and the Technical Inspectorate of an accident or an accident at work which occurs during the handling of or trade in explosive substances and causes the death of or serious physical harm to an employee or physical harm to two or more employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali omanik v&otilde;i valdaja on kohustatud viivitamatult teatama igast l&otilde;hkematerjali varastamise, r&ouml;&ouml;vimise, kaotsimineku v&otilde;i h&auml;vimise juhtumist asukohaj&auml;rgsele politseiasutusele ja Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An owner or possessor of explosive substances is required promptly to notify the local police authority and Technical Inspectorate of every case of theft, robbery, loss or ruin of explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avarii v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse tehnilisi p&otilde;hjusi uurib komisjon, kuhu kuuluvad Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni, T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni, ameti&uuml;hingu ja ettev&otilde;tte esindajad. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The technical reasons for an accident or an accident at work shall be investigated by a committee which is comprised of representatives of the Technical Inspectorate, the Labour Inspectorate, the trade union and the enterprise. </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjoni esimeheks on Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>The representative of the Technical Inspectorate shall be the chairman of the committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui avarii v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse puhul ilmnesid kuriteo tunnused, saadetakse materjal juurdlus- v&otilde;i uurimisorganile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If elements of a criminal offence become evident in an accident or an accident at work, the material shall be sent to an investigation authority. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemisega tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for damage caused by handling of explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamise, l&otilde;hkematerjaliga t&ouml;&ouml;tamise, l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml; tegemise, samuti ilutulestiku korraldamise loa valdaja on kohustatud t&auml;ielikult h&uuml;vitama k&otilde;ik l&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemisega tekitatud kahjud, kui tellija ja t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;tja omavaheline leping ei s&auml;testa teisiti, olenemata sellest, kas kahju tekkimist v&otilde;is ette n&auml;ha v&otilde;i mitte. </eesti>
<inglise>The holder of a permit for the manufacture of an explosive substance, for work with explosive substances, for blasting operations or for the organisation of fireworks displays is required to compensate in full for any damage caused by the handling of explosive substances unless the contract between the customer and the contractor provides otherwise, regardless of whether or not the damage was foreseeable. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 53. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 53. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemise ja k&auml;ibega seotud objektide, ettev&otilde;tete ning asutuste &uuml;levaatus </eesti>
<inglise>Survey of sites, enterprises and agencies involved in handling of and trade in explosive substances </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemise ja k&auml;ibega seotud objektid, ettev&otilde;tted ja asutused kuuluvad kohustuslikule &uuml;levaatusele Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooni poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Sites, enterprises and agencies involved in the handling of and trade in explosive substances are subject to mandatory inspection by the Technical Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;levaatuse sagedus kehtestatakse majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The frequency of inspection shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>9. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 9 </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve ja vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>State Supervision and Liability </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 54. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 54. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse t&auml;itmise riikliku j&auml;relevalve korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of state supervision over implementation of Act </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetest kinnipidamise &uuml;le teostavad: </eesti>
<inglise>State supervision over compliance with the requirements of this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof shall be exercised as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon - l&otilde;hkematerjali ohutu k&auml;itlemise ning t&ouml;&ouml;kohas toimuva veo &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the Technical Inspectorate shall supervise the safe handling of explosive substances and the carriage thereof at jobsites; </inglise>
<eesti>2) politseiasutused - l&otilde;hkematerjali veo &uuml;le &uuml;ldkasutataval teel ning l&otilde;hkematerjalitehase ja -lao valvere&zcaron;iimi ja p&uuml;rotehniliste toodete m&uuml;&uuml;gi ja kasutamise &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>2) police authorities shall supervise the carriage of explosive substances on public roads and the security regimes of explosive substances plants and stores and the sale and use of pyrotechnic articles; </inglise>
<eesti>(10.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.10.2001 entered into force 01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </inglise>
<eesti>3) tarbijakaitseseadusega (RT I 1994, 2, 13; RT I 1999, 35, 450; 102, 907; 2000, 40, 252; 59, 379; 2001, 50, 283 ja 289; 56, 332) volitatud kontrollorganid I ja II klassi p&uuml;rotehniliste toodete jaem&uuml;&uuml;gi &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>3) inspection bodies authorised by the Consumer Protection Act (RT I 1994, 2, 13; RT I 1999, 35, 450; 102, 907; 2000, 40, 252; 59, 379; 2001, 50, 283 and 289; 56, 332) shall supervise the retail trade of pyrotechnic articles of divisions I and II; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tolliasutused - tolliseadustiku ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud korras - l&otilde;hkematerjali sisse- ja v&auml;ljaveo ning transiidi &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>4) customs authorities shall supervise the import, export and transit of explosive substances pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Customs Code and legislation issued on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>5) tulet&otilde;rjej&auml;relevalveorganid - l&otilde;hkematerjalitehase ja -lao tuleohutuse &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>5) fire fighting supervisory bodies shall supervise the fire safety of explosive substances plants and stores; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kohalik omavalitsus vastavalt planeerimis- ja ehitusseadusele - l&otilde;hkematerjalitehase ja -lao ehituse &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>6) local governments shall supervise the construction of explosive substances plants and stores pursuant to the Planning and Building Act; </inglise>
<eesti>7) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsioon - t&ouml;&ouml;kaitseseadusega ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the Labour Inspectorate shall supervise working conditions provided for in the Labour Protection Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>8) Tervisekaitseinspektsioon - l&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemisel tervisekaitse n&otilde;uetest kinnipidamise &uuml;le, l&auml;htudes rahvatervise seadusest (RT I 1995, 57, 978; 1996, 3, 56; 49, 953; 1997, 37/38, 569; 1999, 30, 415; 88, 804; 2001, 23, 128). </eesti>
<inglise>8) the Health Protection Inspectorate shall supervise compliance with health protection requirements in the handling of explosive substances on the basis of the Public Health Act (RT I 1995, 57, 978; 1996, 3, 56; 49, 953; 1997, 37/38, 569; 1999, 30, 415; 88, 804; 2001, 23, 128). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 55. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 55. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalvet teostava ametiisiku &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of supervisory officials </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevast seadusest ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidest kinnipidamise &uuml;le kontrollima volitatud ametiisikul on &otilde;igus vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 54 s&auml;testatud p&auml;devusele ja oma asutuse p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud p&auml;devuse piires: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Officials authorised to monitor compliance with this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof have, pursuant to the competence provided for in &sect; 54 of this Act and within the limits of the competence established by the statutes of their agencies, the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kontrollida k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 60 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud korras kehtestatud l&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemisega seotud tehniliste ja ohutuseeskirjade j&auml;rgimist kontrollialuses ettev&otilde;ttes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) monitor compliance with technical and safety rules related to the handling of explosive substances, established pursuant to the procedure provided in subsection 60 (1) of this Act, in enterprises subject to monitoring; </inglise>
<eesti>2) n&otilde;uda f&uuml;&uuml;siliselt isikult v&otilde;i juriidilise isiku v&otilde;i asutuse vastutavalt esindajalt k&otilde;igi l&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemisega seotud dokumentide esitamist ja kirjalikku v&otilde;i suulist informatsiooni, mis on vajalik kontrolli l&auml;biviimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) require natural persons or representatives of legal persons or agencies to present all documentation concerning the handling of explosive substances and written or oral information necessary to conduct an inspection; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teha ettekirjutusi avastatud &otilde;iguserikkumise l&otilde;petamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) issue precepts for the elimination of discovered offences; </inglise>
<eesti>4) m&auml;&auml;rata ekspertiisi avarii v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse p&otilde;hjuse v&auml;ljaselgitamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) order expert analysis for the identification of the reasons for accidents and accidents at work; </inglise>
<eesti>5) v&otilde;tta tarvitusele muid abin&otilde;usid, mis on ette n&auml;htud seaduste ja nende alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega. </eesti>
<inglise>5) take other measures prescribed by Acts and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inimese elu ja tervist ohustava v&otilde;i avariiohtliku t&ouml;&ouml; tegemisel, samuti ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmisel j&auml;relevalvet teostava ametiasutuse esindajal on &otilde;igus seisatada t&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A representative of a supervisory administrative agency has the right to suspend work which endangers human life or health or is unsafe, or upon non-compliance with a precept. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 56. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 56. </inglise>
<eesti>Kontrollitava ja kontrollija kohustused j&auml;relevalve tagamiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of inspected and inspector to ensure supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ettev&otilde;te v&otilde;i asutus peab v&otilde;imaldama kontrollijal tutvuda k&otilde;igi kontrollimiseks vajalike dokumentidega ning andma talle vajalikku teavet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Enterprises and agencies shall enable inspectors to examine all documents necessary for inspection and provide them with necessary information. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kontrollija peab hoidma kontrolli k&auml;igus teavitunud &auml;risaladust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Inspectors shall maintain any business secrets which become known to them in the course of inspection. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 57. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 57. </inglise>
<eesti>F&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of natural persons </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide rikkumise eest kannab f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik tsiviil-, haldus- v&otilde;i kriminaalvastutust seaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Natural persons shall bear civil, administrative or criminal liability for violations of this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 58. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 58. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of legal persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juriidilise isiku halduskaristus on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Administrative penalties for legal persons are as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) rahatrahv 10 000 kuni 50 000 krooni l&otilde;hkematerjali m&uuml;&uuml;mise eest l&otilde;hkematerjali soetusluba mitteomavale isikule (v&auml;lja arvatud I ja II klassi p&uuml;rotehniliste toodete m&uuml;&uuml;misel); </eesti>
<inglise>1) a fine of between 10 000 and 50 000 kroons is imposed for the sale of explosive substances to a person who does not hold an explosive substances procurement permit (except for the sale of pyrotechnic articles of divisions I and II); </inglise>
<eesti>1 (1)) rahatrahv 1000 kuni 10 000 krooni I ja II klassi p&uuml;rotehniliste toodete jaem&uuml;&uuml;gil kehtivate piirangute rikkumise eest; </eesti>
<inglise>1 (1)) a fine of between 1000 and 10 000 kroons is imposed for the violation of the restrictions of sale of pyrotechnic articles of divisions I and II; </inglise>
<eesti>(10.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.10.2001 entered into force 01.11.2001 - RT I 2001, 85, 510) </inglise>
<eesti>2) rahatrahv 10 000 kuni 70 000 krooni loata l&otilde;hket&ouml;&ouml;de tegemise v&otilde;i ilutulestiku korraldamise eest (v&auml;lja arvatud I ja II klassi p&uuml;rotehniliste toodete kasutamisega); </eesti>
<inglise>2) a fine of between 10 000 and 70 000 kroons is imposed for blasting or the organisation of fireworks displays without an appropriate permit (except for the use of pyrotechnic articles of divisions I and II); </inglise>
<eesti>3) rahatrahv 10 000 kuni 30 000 krooni j&auml;relevalveorgani ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a fine of between 10 000 and 30 000 kroons is imposed for failure to comply with a precept issued by a supervisory body; </inglise>
<eesti>4) rahatrahv 10 000 kuni 50 000 krooni avarii, t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse v&otilde;i l&otilde;hkematerjali kaotsimineku juhtumi varjamise eest; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a fine of between 10 000 and 50 000 kroons is imposed for the concealment of an incident involving an accident, accident at work or loss of explosive substances; </inglise>
<eesti>5) rahatrahv 5000 kuni 25 000 krooni l&otilde;hkematerjali hoidmise ja arvestuse n&otilde;uete rikkumise eest; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a fine of between 5000 and 25 000 kroons is imposed for the violation of requirements concerning the storage and recording of explosive substances; </inglise>
<eesti>6) rahatrahv 1000 kuni 10 000 krooni l&otilde;hkematerjali arvestusraamatute kaotamise v&otilde;i ennet&auml;htaegse h&auml;vitamise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>6) a fine of between 1000 and 10 000 kroons is imposed for the loss or premature destruction of a ledger of explosive substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juriidilise isiku poolt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud &otilde;iguserikkumise asja arutamise ja temale karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igus on halduskohtunikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Administrative court judges have the right to hear and impose penalties for matters concerning offences specified in subsection (1) of this section by legal persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Menetlus k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 loetletud juriidiliste isikute haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste asjades, kaasa arvatud karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramine ja vaidlustamine ning j&otilde;ustunud halduskaristuse otsuse t&auml;itmine toimub haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustikus (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453) ja t&auml;itemenetluse seadustikus (RT I 1993, 49, 693; RT I 2001, 29, 156; 43, 238) etten&auml;htud korras, kui k&auml;esolev seadus ei s&auml;testa teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Proceedings in administrative offence matters of legal persons set out in subsection (1) of this section, including the imposition and contestation of penalties, and the execution of administrative judgements imposing penalties which have come into force, are carried out pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453) and the Code of Enforcement Procedure (RT I 1993, 49, 693; RT I 2001, 29, 156; 43, 238), unless otherwise provided by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Juriidilise isiku karistamine ei vabasta vastutusest &otilde;iguserikkumises s&uuml;&uuml;diolevat ametiisikut. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Penalisation of a legal person does not release an official who is guilty of an offence from liability. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 59. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 59. </inglise>
<eesti>Haldusprotokolli koostamine </eesti>
<inglise>Preparation of administrative offence reports </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 58 l&otilde;ikes 1 loetletud juriidilise isiku haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste kohta protokolli koostamise &otilde;igus on k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;itmise &uuml;le j&auml;relevalvet teostama volitatud ametiisikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Officials authorised to conduct supervision over the implementation of this Act have the right to prepare reports concerning the administrative offences listed in subsection 58 (1) of this Act by legal persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Protokollis n&auml;idatakse selle koostamise aeg ja koht, asutuse nimi ja aadress, kelle nimel protokoll koostatakse, protokolli koostanud isiku ametinimetus, ees- ja perekonnanimi, haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja nimetus ja asukoht, haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja ees- ja perekonnanimi ning ametikoht, haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise koht, aeg ja kirjeldus, viide k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 58 l&otilde;ike 1 vastavale punktile, mis n&auml;eb ette vastutuse selle haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise eest, haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja seletus ja muud asja lahendamiseks vajalikud andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A report shall set out the time and place of preparation of the report, the name and address of the agency in whose name the report is prepared, the official title, given name and surname of the person who prepares the report, the name and seat of the administrative offender, the given name, surname and title of the representative of the administrative offender, the place, time and description of the administrative offence, a reference to the appropriate clause of subsection 58 (1) of this Act which prescribes liability for the administrative offence, an explanation from the representative of the administrative offender and other information necessary for determination of the matter. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 60. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 60. </inglise>
<eesti>Eeskirjade, juhendite ja &otilde;ppeprogrammide kehtestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment of rules, instructions and curricula </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;hkematerjalitehase ja l&otilde;hkematerjalilao ehitamise ja kasutamise eeskiri, l&otilde;hkematerjali valmistamise, hoidmise ja kasutamise tehnilised ja ohutuseeskirjad ning p&uuml;rotehniliste toodete k&auml;itlemise eeskiri kehtestatakse majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Rules for the construction and use of explosive substances plants and explosive substances stores, technical and safety rules for the manufacture, storage and use of explosive substances and rules for the handling of pyrotechnic articles shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;hkematerjali ohutu k&auml;itlemise ja k&auml;ibe ettev&otilde;ttesisesed juhendid kehtestab ettev&otilde;tja koosk&otilde;lastatult Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooniga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Written internal policies of enterprises for the safe handling of and trade in explosive substances shall be established by traders in concordance with the Technical Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;hkematerjali k&auml;itlemise ja k&auml;ibe eest vastutavate isikute v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe ja t&auml;iend&otilde;ppe, l&otilde;hkajate, l&otilde;hkematerjali laojuhatajate, v&auml;ljaandjate ja laborantide &otilde;ppeprogrammid kehtestab &otilde;ppusi l&auml;biviiv koolitusasutus koosk&otilde;lastatult Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsiooniga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Curricula for training and in-service training for persons responsible for the handling of and trade in explosive substances and curricula for blasters, heads of explosive substances stores, issuers of explosive substances and explosive substances laboratory assistants shall be established by the educational and training institution conducting the training and concorded with the Technical Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 61. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 61. </inglise>
<eesti>Dokumentide vormide kinnitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Approval of standard format of documentation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 3, 9, 19, 23, 36, 37 ja 38 s&auml;testatud lubade, k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 25 s&auml;testatud t&ouml;&ouml;k&auml;su, k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 27 s&auml;testatud raamatute ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 30, 41, 42 ja 43 s&auml;testatud tunnistuste vormid kinnitatakse majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The standard format of permits provided for in &sect;&sect; 3, 9, 19, 23, 36, 37 and 38 of this Act, work orders provided for in &sect; 25 of this Act, ledgers provided for in &sect; 27 of this Act and certificates provided for in &sect;&sect; 30, 41, 42 and 43 of this Act shall be approved by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 16 s&auml;testatud loa vorm kinnitatakse siseministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The standard format of the permit provided for in &sect; 16 of this Act shall be approved by a regulation of the Minister of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 62. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 62. </inglise>
<eesti>Toimingute maksustamine riigil&otilde;ivuga </eesti>
<inglise>Taxation of operations with state fee </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud toimingute eest tasutakse riigil&otilde;ivu vastavalt riigil&otilde;ivuseadusele. </eesti>
<inglise>A state fee shall be paid on operations provided for in this Act pursuant to the State Fees Act. </inglise>
